postshot_description: good beams, large IRE at 0.22s, plasma disrupts at 0.355s 12ms after an event killing the H-mode, SS beam inhibit worked fine.

preshot_description: repeat with SW beam hopefully
postshot_description: good beam, but no H-mode, not clear why not. It might have been shot history. Compared to 17509 it had the same density, but higher beam power and EFCB on. There are some dithers at 0.173 though.

postshot_description: Good shot.

preshot_description: Repeat

postshot_description: Excellent beams. Major density loss at 0.320, rather weak H mode. Good density and Ip match.

preshot_description: repeat, maybe wall conditions will be better. Reduce HFS plenum to 1.5 Bar(1.6)
postshot_description: another decent pair of beams. similar result except that the locked mode terminated the plasma instead of just shedding density. SS startup delayed.

preshot_description: repeat using HFS up/down valves under feedback control.
postshot_description: More good beams. Earlier H mode, but earlier termination also. Some good Elms. Increasing OII levels especially just prior to termination.

preshot_description: Shift Zref down to -1.5cm(+0.5).
postshot_description: Density rolling down after 0.260 despite the best efforts of the gas supply.

preshot_description: increase dRref to increase inner gap, and bring SW beam earlier.
postshot_description: Another 2 good beams. OK but not much changed

preshot_description: repeat with sw 50ms earlier again. Shut off gas at 0.130.
postshot_description: Bad shot. severe IRE at 0.190.

preshot_description: Extend fuelling until 0.200
postshot_description: Better, similar to 17555, no H mode.

preshot_description: Invoke HFS mid-plane gas.
postshot_description: Full length despite IRE at 0.190 (hitting N beam dump at this time).  SS beam a bit late, so no beam during Ip ramp. No H mode again.

preshot_description: retry

preshot_description: disable HFS midplane gas, and move Zref up to -0.5cm
postshot_description: Good beams (again) Not very different plasma, IRE at 0.200 though not quite as bad. Disrupt at 0.320.

preshot_description: Revert to Z=-1.5cm. RAISE MAIN PLENUM PRESSURE TO 1.77 BAR (max), reduce prefill flow to compensate.

preshot_description: Standard shot
postshot_description: Rather short

preshot_description:

Replace density reference with waveform from 17039, plus added point at (0.2, 2e20).

No i/b gas.

preshot_description:
Whoops - didn't set density feedback for last shot. Turn it on...
Disable o/b gas from 100 ms.
Enable divertor fuelling from 100 ms.
postshot_description:
Beams both worked.
Density just reaches reference (and overshoots) by the end of the shot at 350 ms.
Switchover in fuelling regimes shows in density droop at 100 ms.
H-mode from 260 ms.

preshot_description: Try again

preshot_description:
Return end of o/b fuelling to 100 ms, from 150.
Add i/b gas, starting 50 ms earlier than normal, for 500 ms.
I_p reduced to 700 kA
postshot_description:
Density still doesn't rise rapidly enough.
H-mode late and unreliable.
Strikes beam dump hard when HOMER fails after 300 ms.

preshot_description: Repeat with sensitivity parameter decreased in HOMER algorithm (courtesy J. Storrs)
postshot_description: Still doesn't leave CC until 300 ms.

preshot_description:
Trying to work out why the plasma isn't leaving the CC when it was earlier. HOMER is fine. Plasma control magnetic signals are fine. All a bit stumped here.

Try increasing DRREF by 4 cm for all peak points.
postshot_description: Plasma now clears CC (though not by much) from 185 ms on, with a brief relapse at 240 ms.

preshot_description:
The fruits of Geof's analysis are reaped - try:
i) Increasing IDIV in range 70-200 ms
and ii) Allowing a little more early V_loop
postshot_description: Detaches nicely now, but H-mode is still too late for the PIC's tastes.

preshot_description: Increase I_p ramp to move flat-top earlier by 30 ms. Increase LV peak length by 30 ms. Move NBI earlier by 30ish ms.
postshot_description:
I_p flat-top slants throughout - overshoots by 50 kA initially.
H-mode starts at 200 ms now, and the ELMs are *great*.

preshot_description: Adjust V_loop to peak of 4V initially, and match demand later on more closely (i.e. more drop). Extra demand means last point has to move forward to 450 ms.
postshot_description: Vloop mods over-done, resulting in excessive early Ip and hitting the walls. Also SW beam rather short.  Otherwise not too bad.

preshot_description: Restore 17580 and set SW cutoff and TS to 0.340
postshot_description: good beames and shot, unfortunately lost H mode at 0.310 - sawtooth, perhaps?

preshot_description:
very small incraese to Idiv and shift Zref down. repeat with measurement at 0.290.
Vloop needs significant tuning, but leave it for now.
postshot_description: good beams and OK shot -fell right out of H mode between 0.210 and 0.240 instead of just getting weaker.  But, good measurements so this will do for now.

preshot_description: retry

preshot_description: delay HFS gas to 944+60, raise Idiv slightly to lift off c/c
postshot_description: good beams. Early disruption - not clear why. much better inner gap and early Ip and density, still below par at LH time.

preshot_description: Restore standard plasma shot 17262.

postshot_description: Reasonable shot, good NBI.

preshot_description: Repeat, adjusting VLOOP.
postshot_description: Shot ended earlier.

postshot_description: Good shot.

preshot_description: Restore shot 15500. Increase initial VLOOP. SS NBI enabled.

preshot_description: Restore shot 17518. Enable SS NBI.
postshot_description: Good shot and NBI.

postshot_description: Loss of vertical control just after 0.100s - NBI cut out OK. Ip was better until then, though still a bit high. FAs cutout about 0.095. P2XO failed again.

preshot_description: restore 17583 (150ms Ip ramp) PCS crashed, unclear why, restarted OK.

preshot_description: repeat

preshot_description: repeat

preshot_description: repeat

preshot_description: repeat

preshot_description: try again.

preshot_description: repeat with different pellet size

postshot_description: Pellet-induced ELM-free H-mode! betaT>12% (briefly), 160kJ plasma energy. Greenish plasma in Elm-free, the only VUV impurity lines going up fast are OVI (CIII may be saturated)

preshot_description: repeat without pellet
postshot_description: good long shot, good fast cut in SW. Weak H mode only - no sawteeth but many chirping modes.

preshot_description:

preshot_description: repeat
postshot_description: SS beam chopped 0.190-0.230. Pellet killed shot again, at 0.250. Fairly deep penetration. Omaha signals all seem to be dead.

preshot_description: try smaller pellets.

postshot_description: Damn me. Good beam and density up, but not H mode.  betaT>9% for 0.100s+. Vessel neutral pressure is 2-3 times higher than 16373, and plasma density is 30% higher also, despite lower input. Also close to c/c. Benign MHD (killed by sawtooth?)

preshot_description: shorten LFS gas and raise HFS pressure. Raise Idiv slightly.
postshot_description: Sudden death at 0.260. Density stopped rising at 0.240 due to mode which stopped. neutral pressure increased, unfortunately. This shot has less inner gap, higher li, and higher beta at the end of the Ip ramp -all opposite to expectation.

preshot_description: go back to 17632 (no HFS gas) and try again with small pellet.

preshot_description: try again
postshot_description: another excellent L mode shot. Small pellet arrived a little late. ane fringe hop at end gives bad status - fixable. Solid 10% betaT for 99ms.

preshot_description: one last go, with a Vloop notch at 0.300.
postshot_description: Again good L mode shot - slightly less beta. A couple of brief H modes, triggered neither by Vloop dip nor by pellet, but by chirp which also triggered sustained mode - as in previous shot. I still think this is too close to c/c, despite 17638.

preshot_description: Standard shot
postshot_description: Ah damn, forgot to turn the i/b gas puff back on; result - grows way under-dense and disrupts at 300 ms.

preshot_description: As beams are taking a long time, run the standard shot again, this time with i/b gas
postshot_description: Odd - density is still low, even with i/b gas, and again we have a locked mode after 300 ms.

preshot_description:

SW 50-350 ms
No SS
postshot_description:
Like 17609, falls over very early again, loses vertical stability at 90 ms while highly elongated.
Good SW beam.
P2XO error (at time plasma failed).

Move I_p f/b earlier, to 30 ms.
Move n_e f/b earlier, to 50 ms.
Ease ramps of both I_p and n_e.
postshot_description:
That's much better...
Nearly 400 ms shot, big and chunky, R_out = 1.45 m.
Elongation peaks at only 2.2, though, and stabilises at 1.9-2.0.

preshot_description:

Should have SS beam as well this time.
postshot_description:
Beams good, shot similar. No H-mode.
Why did it terminate when it did? Perhaps because last V_loop point is at 350 ms, signalling end of P1.

postshot_description:

SW fails at 240 ms, prompting a big IRE.
Still no H-mode.

preshot_description:

Add i/b gas at 1.6 B.
postshot_description:
Density grows throughout.
Disrupts slightly before 400 ms, after striking the beam dump.

preshot_description: Move R_out flat-top to begin at 120 ms
postshot_description: Ramp-up too ambitious, loses stability and disrupts at 120 ms.

preshot_description: Restore R_out ramp, move in
postshot_description:

IRE at 210 ms.

Repeat

preshot_description: And again, pumped m-HFS gas lines before the shot

preshot_description: repeat after 5min GDC, pump out m-HFS gas lines before plasma
postshot_description: good long shot, real time density has fringe jump, plenum pressure in PCS  was set to 2.1 bar rather than 1.5bar as set in the plenum

preshot_description: Restored 17678, gas and density from  17674, start feed-back from 25ms rather than 50ms, small changes to DRREF and IP to get better match, EFCB set to 0., SW and SS start at 0.1s
postshot_description: good beams, although SS is late by , late L/H transition at 0.217s, hick-up in the density ramp-up at change over between LFS and HFS puffing, H-mode is lost 0.301s

preshot_description: bring overlap t/b-HFS puffing with LFS by bringing HFS puffing on 20ms earlier, reduced IDIV after 0.3s
postshot_description: delayed H-mode transition to 0.295s, higher density during ramp-up

preshot_description:
Model density trace to macthc ANE from 17702, reduce IDIV after 0.3s further
 (its almost flat now)
postshot_description: H-mode 20ms later, but 10ms longer, a UFO at 0.13s IDIV isn't matched very well

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: density feed-back failed

preshot_description: Use Flow control with target flow modelled from 17704 except for feed-back oscillations
postshot_description: Late H-mode, good beams, LFS flow rate too high

preshot_description: reduce LFS flow to 15 before 0.1s, switch off EFCB
postshot_description: no SW beam, very late H-mode

preshot_description: repeat with SW
postshot_description: good beams, LH transition at 0.212s as in 17702, H-mode lost at 0.31s, just before the first sawtooth which is at 0.314s, IDIV match is still abysmal, but don't want to change the loop voltage

preshot_description: add EFCB from ramping to -2kA from 0.2s to 0.22s
postshot_description: good shot, H-mode delayed by 24ms, similar ELMs

preshot_description: increase EFCB to ramp to -4kA from 0.2s to 0.24s
postshot_description: no SW beam, compared to 17708 it has a longer H-mode with only a few ELMs, the L/H transition is at 0.299s rather than at 0.310s, very long shot, some wall interaction during ramp down phase. There are actually STI H-mode pphases after 0.37s

preshot_description: repeat with SW
postshot_description: both beam, but SS a bit late, no H-mode, density is higher from 0.14s, because of the automatic gas puff at the end of the shot.

preshot_description: EFCB current to reach -1kA at 0.21s.
postshot_description: SS beam late, no H-mode before 0.296s, the density is lower than in #17712, but still higher than in #17709

preshot_description: EFCB to -3kA reached at 0.23.
postshot_description: SS bad again, late start and cut aout between 0.2s and 0.24s, H-mode from 0.285s with few ELMs, the large ELMs are saw tooth driven. Interesting shot though. Density is spot on again.

preshot_description: repeat to get good SS beam
postshot_description: both beams OK, H-mode transition at 0.23s lost just 10ms later, this could be due to the applied error field, destabilising a locked mode.

preshot_description: repeat with -2.5 kA (reached at 0.225s)
postshot_description: good shots, good beams, "early" H-mode for this scenario, there seem to be fewer ELMs more separated with respect to 17709

preshot_description: Repeat with EFCB current -275 kA reached at 0.228s
postshot_description: No H-mode, EFCB probably too high, density is spot on.

preshot_description:
Set SS start to 50 ms and SW to 100 ms 
use inboard upper and lower valves rather than the mid-plane
modify gas puffs in start up to match the standard shot
postshot_description: 320 ms shot - SW short  - IP startup poor - density quite a good match maybe slightly low

preshot_description: increase feed back window - increase outboard radius by 4cm to keep off cc - turn off EFFCB - increase vloop by 0.5 in start and get Ip to match ramp
postshot_description: 280ms shot - large ELM free H-mode until event which causes disruption H-mode from 200ms then ELM free to 260 ms - 13 % Betat

preshot_description: Bring flat top IP 20 ms earlier - turn on nner upper and lower valves 20 ms earlier to try to increase density
postshot_description: Much shorter H-mode - no effect on density

preshot_description:
reload SS start at 70 ms SW at 200 ms - change gas puff and add inner upper and lower 
 Reference => 11535.
postshot_description: 300ms shot - H-mode from 250 ms after the second beam comes on - otherwise good match from the reference

preshot_description:
repeat without SW beam to try to match 11535
 Reference => 11535.
postshot_description: 290 ms shot - L-mode throughout - short sharp disruption

preshot_description:
Start SS at 0 for 400 ms - and run without SW again
 Reference => 11535.
postshot_description: SS started at 120 ms

preshot_description:
repeat to get full length ss only shot
 Reference => 11535.
postshot_description: good beam from the beginning - good sharp disruption

preshot_description:
add SW at 150 ms and change zref from 0.5 to +1.0 cm
 Reference => 11535.
postshot_description: both beams - L-mode - sharp disruption  - good n=1 finger seen on the photron camera

preshot_description:
repeat to get better IR data
 Reference => 11535.
postshot_description: good shot - good IR and photron camera data of the disruption

preshot_description:
reduce zref to +0.5 to try to get into H-mode

postshot_description: good H-mode from 220 ms drops out of H-mode before it disrupts

preshot_description:
start SW 50 ms earlier at 0.1 s
 Reference => 11535.

preshot_description:
change zref to +1.0 to keep in L-mode and drop the field to 0.52 T
 Reference => 11535.
postshot_description: good shot good beam - good sharp disruption good camera data - disrupted early as expected due to lower field

preshot_description: standard Plasma shot after 7 min glow
postshot_description: 300 ms shot - HeII level slightly higher than 17700 the previous standard shot but the Oxygen levels are twice as high following the leak

preshot_description: Reload shot 14639 - try Ohmically while waiting for the beam - switch to using Density feedback all the while after 50 ms
postshot_description: 150 ms shot - strong interaction on P3 - oxygen lines much more prominent than reference - even before the plasma was pushed down

preshot_description: change zref from -14 to -10 - adjust the density trace to match what was achieved during the first 50ms
postshot_description: better match to refernce in zref but still looses vertical control at 160 ms

preshot_description: delay zref by 20ms - reduce zpgain - add beams SS at 30 ms and SW at 200 ms
postshot_description: 350 ms shot - The zpush started and then stopped at 70ms as the FAs cut out - then they restarted at 250 ms and pushed the zref down after that

preshot_description: Start SW earlier at 130 ms
postshot_description: Sort SW - 350 ms shot - Z shift the same FAs seem to cut out due to chirps

preshot_description: Reduce deriv gain to 0.25 and also put in a notch around the trouble region
postshot_description: 450 ms shot - Zref did work - Hmode from 300 ms - touches P3 from 160 to 240 ms

preshot_description: reduce P5/p4 to 0.5 before 250 ms and increase Idiv in this period to try to keep plasma off the P3 coil
postshot_description: No SS - 400 ms SW - 320 ms shot - better shape in the period before 200 ms

preshot_description: reapet to get both beams
postshot_description: SS again failed - SW 400 ms

preshot_description: Carry on with SW only - reduce Density by 30%
postshot_description: 400 ms shot - good beam

preshot_description: repeat to get both beams
postshot_description: SS started a bit late - 420 ms shot - good low density - no H-mode - Plasma current starts to drop at 400 ms- due to last point in vloop at 400 ms

preshot_description: add last point in vloop at 500 ms - increase P1PS enable to 0.85 - in crease TF flat top to 500 ms - increase Idiv in period around 150ms to stop plasma touching P3
postshot_description: 2 beams - SS late agin - current still ramps down at  400 ms - problem now is the gains window

preshot_description: extend feedback window for the entire shot
postshot_description: FAs cut out at 0.155, slow VDE terminates at 0.270.

preshot_description: retry, but revert to LFS fuelling for improved response time.
postshot_description: Wondershot! 0.545 s long (flattop till 0.475), tho' only 0.200 from SW. Beam dump temp peaks at 650C according to PCS. Measurable HXR emission throughout. Lost FA2 at 0.150, ran on FA1 for rest of shot!

preshot_description: raise density ref 20%.
postshot_description: lost both FAs at 0.155, plasma returns to midplane (?!) then disrupts at 0.250.

preshot_description: try again with Zd gain=0.1(0.2)
postshot_description: Another little cracker. Full 0.500 flattop (limit of f/f w/fs), Goes into H mode at 0.380, gas shuts off just afterwards. Plasma bouncing a bit but not much worse than 17742.

preshot_description: extend shot to 0.550 (limited by I2t and P1PS enable)
postshot_description: Flux consuption reduced - ran into TF limit

preshot_description: retry
postshot_description: long shot, H mode after 0.300. Only 0.100 from SW. Fails to rampdown - unclear why( no magnetics data after 0.500)

preshot_description: retry
postshot_description: Excellent. H mode earlier (as expected). Signs of mode activity and again failed to ramp down.

preshot_description: Repeat standard test shot.
postshot_description: OK. 300 ms. Oxigen level lower than on the previous day, but still high.

preshot_description: Reload 17748.
postshot_description: OK. Nice Ohmic reference.

preshot_description: Repeat with a change in the vertical position. (From -10 cm to 0 cm).
postshot_description: Another Ohmic shot.

preshot_description: Reload 17748. This time with NBI.
postshot_description: OK, longer shot, but SW beam very short.

preshot_description: Repeat with SS beam only.
postshot_description: OK. Shot longer than 0.5 s. Goes into H-mode at 0.4 s.

preshot_description: Repeat with SW NBI.
postshot_description: OK. Both beams worked. Shot enters H-mode at about 0.35 s.

preshot_description: Reduced Z position from -10 cm to -5 cm and increased outer radius by 1.5 cm.
postshot_description: No SW NBI. Apart from that nice shot.

preshot_description: Increased the outer radius by 1.5 cm at the beginning of the discharge.
postshot_description: OK. Good shot.

preshot_description: Increased Z position to -1 cm. Decreased outer radius by 2 cm at the beginning of the shot and by 1 cm towards the end.
postshot_description: Again no SW NBI.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: OK. IRE at 0.254 s.

preshot_description: Reload 17761. Extended TF to 0.6 s. Changed Z position from -10 cm to 10 cm.
postshot_description: No SS NBI. I forgot to apply the changes to plasma vertical position. Z still -10 cm.

preshot_description: Repeat with  right vertical position (10 cm).
postshot_description: OK. Huge flux consumption. Shots ends at 0.36 s.

preshot_description: Reloaded 17761. Switched from Ip to Vloop feedback at 0.150 s, aiming at 0 Vloop after 0.150 s.
postshot_description: Ip decaying more-or-less.

preshot_description: Increased flat-top current to 420 kA. Increased loop voltage by 50% before 0.150 s.
postshot_description: Plasma current still not sustained.

preshot_description: Reload 17767. Set TS time at 280 ms.
postshot_description: OK, although not very long because of high flux consumption.

preshot_description: Reload 13369 but convert from gas1 and inboard HP puff to density control with piezo-only fuelling. SS is set to fire from 100ms but NOT selected in PCS.
postshot_description: Initial density somewhat lower than reference shot. Ip flattop rather ropey.

preshot_description: Increase prefill to drive full PV voltage starting 1ms earlier. Repeat with PINI still deselected.
postshot_description: Initial density is better, might benefit from density feedback starting earlier. Ip still needs some work.

preshot_description: Reduce NELREF to 1.5e20.
postshot_description: No beam? Why? Slight over shoot in density.

preshot_description: Modify NELREF to try to prevent over shoot in density at 150ms. PINI=59kV
postshot_description: OK, good 150ms flat-top. Density levels off at 1.75e20

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=60kV
Repeat.
postshot_description: Good shot

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=61kV
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=62kV
postshot_description: Beam drops out once (215-240ms).

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=63kV
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat. Reduce PINI voltage=57kV
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: Longer shot but too much ripple on beam voltage.

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=56kV
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=55kV. Set ZD, ZP gains to standard values.
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=54kV
postshot_description: Good shot.

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=53kV
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=52kV
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat. PINI=51kV
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Ohmic standard shot with RP reciprocation, to test the RP
postshot_description: very bad H-mode behaviour, strange loss of density at  0.235s

preshot_description: reload 15729 to test SEBs scenario (other shots should be 17544 and 17545)
postshot_description: went OK, but appears to have a higher density than 17544, also the density is not quite as stable, 15729 has no density measurement, but the core NE from ATM is very similar

preshot_description: Reload 17650, change ZREF from 0.7 to 0.5, RP reciprocation disabled, RP moved out of the way, no SS beam due to HV problems after the area entry (do shape development without beam)
postshot_description: 0.35s shot, full P1 swing, interaction on both P3 coils, outer radius seems to be a bit less than in 17650, no IRE, very balanced according to EFIT, a bit low initially

preshot_description: decrease IDIV by 2.5kA from 0.2s, ramp SHAPE from 1.5 to 2 between 0.25s to 0.5s, set ZREF to  0.7 between 0.05s, and 0.15s, ramp to 0.5 between 0.15s and 0.2s, SS NBI 1.8MW from 0.05 to 0.45
postshot_description: good NBI, 0.55s shot, IRE at 0.23, vertical position slightly up, interaction with CC from 0.35s

preshot_description: increase ROUT to 1.5s, reaching flat-top at 0.23 rather than at 0.25, restore IDIV from 17793, increase shape to 2, main plenum pressure to 2.425bar
postshot_description: prefill gas too high, since prefill is not under flow control , bad plasma start-up, disrupts at 0.29s due to a mode locking

preshot_description: prefill under flow control (first time I did this keep fingers crossed), remove shape ramp after 0.25s
postshot_description: disrupts at 0.35s, no good density flat-top, better start-up, deviation of Ip when P2 current goes negative, this may be due to the fact that IDIV is higher than the demand at this time, this shot ran with density feedback from -0.06 just fine

preshot_description: increase IDIV according to achieved IDIV because if P2 switch over, because the best P3 interaction was at 0.23s, start density control at 0.0s, adjust density reference to achieved density
postshot_description: slightly lower density, disrupts at 0.123s, loose FAs at 0.11s

preshot_description: reload old NELREF from 17796 with minor change after 0.17s,
postshot_description: disrupts at the same time due to Fa's

preshot_description: Reduce ZDGAIN between 0.08s and 0.148s from the elevated level of 0.35 to the normal level at 0.3
postshot_description: 0.3s shot, density is flat between

preshot_description: Repeat with RP reciprocating, and lower flow rate to keep the density flat
postshot_description: 0.35s shot, Hard X-ray alarm (1.25, KS says ignore today), good RP reciprocation

preshot_description: repeat with RP further in by 1cm
postshot_description: good repeat, but RP not far enough in

preshot_description: repeat with RP in by 2cm
postshot_description: good repeat, RP better, but still judged to be too far out, PCS indicated unacceptable offset on P3L rogowsky

preshot_description: increase density by 50% and program ramp down from 0.29s
postshot_description: good shot, plasma disrupts at 0.297s before the ramp-down has any real effect, target density not fully achieved, since gas flow of the HFS puffs is not sufficient and hence the density lags behind strangely even with the LFS puffs, no real density flat-top.

preshot_description: repeat with probe 1cm further in
postshot_description: good shot again

preshot_description: Adjust settings for magnetic feedback. Also increase loop volts to improve startup
postshot_description: plasma survives but overcooked the Ip ramp-up. Touches the wall then sags back then expands again. P2 hits zero.

preshot_description: Curtail Vloop, fix up Bv to better match feedback, adjust density reference, enable P2 reversing and flatten IDIV.
postshot_description: still not looking great. Poor radial and Ip feedback, but doesn't get over-sized

preshot_description: Start Ip feedback quite early and straighten up Vloop to reduce feed-forward impact. Adjust 'knee' of Bv waveform to try to avoid ringing
postshot_description: Still a poor start-up. Realise it was because initial Ip is below 'detection threshold' to enable Ip feedback.

preshot_description: Reduce Ip threshold to 50kA and extinction threshold to 30kA. Tweak Vloop and extend IDIV ramp until it is 5kA higher.
postshot_description: A bit better but the shape still doesn't look like it will give us what we want.

preshot_description: Change tack - repeat NBI-heated L-mode shot 17610 but with density feedback starting later
postshot_description: NBI had 2 retries at the beginning, identical to the restored shot! Lower density before later start of feedback helped Ip to pull up.

preshot_description: Adjust Vloop and enable P2 reversing. Reduce IDIV and remove drop in DRREF
postshot_description: Looks better - touches CC after about 250ms and then disrupts.

preshot_description: Reduce density reference and ramp up drref a bit
postshot_description: got a huge density due to loss of interferometer with density feedback.

preshot_description: repeat, albeit probably with walls loaded with D2 from previous shot.
postshot_description: held off CC for a bit longer and plasma lasts longer

preshot_description: 1st boronisation recovery shot
postshot_description: A nice start, 560 ms shot, impurities not too high, gas demand similar to reference (17423)

preshot_description: 2nd boronisation recovery shot
postshot_description: Impurities decreasing

preshot_description: 3rd boronisation recovery shot
postshot_description: Impurities and gas demand still decreasing a little, but nearly stabilised

preshot_description: Try again
postshot_description:
Very long shot (600 ms).
Edge not stable enough for probe (200-300 ms period).

preshot_description: Restore DRREF from 15729
postshot_description: Good enough from 200-300 ms. V_loop finishes at 330 ms, provoking a slow plasma event. Plasma expands outwards at end of shot.

preshot_description:
Round off V_loop to 0, to ease P1 current blip at 330 ms.
Slowly ramp down I_p at end (nominally finishing at 700 ms).
postshot_description:
Unclear whether mods eased matters.
Good shot for probe data.

preshot_description: Repeat with probe changes
postshot_description: Useful shot

preshot_description: Ditto
postshot_description: Ditto

preshot_description: Restore 15724
postshot_description: Better than the reference, but density is quite high

preshot_description: Halve late flowref
postshot_description: Not enough

preshot_description: Halve early flowref
postshot_description: Nearly there

preshot_description: Halve flowref again
postshot_description:
Density much lower, killed by locked mode at ~380 ms.
Too low really; the non-linear response to the change has pushed it down a little below the recommended minimum of 5e19 ne line integral.

preshot_description:
Increase early flowref to 3.5
Increase flowref after 300 ms to 5
postshot_description: Density still on the low side, a further increase will be necessary

preshot_description: Increase flowref by 20% throughout
postshot_description:
Density barely changed! Bah!
And for this shot there is a HXR warning.

preshot_description:
Increase flowref throughout by 25%; a little more than that for the end.
Convert to magnetic radial feedback,
postshot_description: And the density goes down! Geof thinks that we are losing the wall fuelling due to running too many low density shots.

preshot_description: Increase flowref by 40% throughout. We are now at a higher level than one from which we had previously decreased by 50%, but conditions seem to have changed.
postshot_description: Still it is not enough...

preshot_description: Increased flow before 0.3 s to achieve a more sustained density.
postshot_description: OK. Thanks to David's advise density is sustained until 0.3 s.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: OK. Density increasing all the way through the shot.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: OK. Density higher than the shot before, probably we  are starting to load the wall.

preshot_description: Reduce fuelling by 30% and repeat.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Ok. Another good shot.

preshot_description: Drop the current to 450 kA and repeat.
postshot_description: OK. Acceptable density control.

preshot_description: Drop fuelling by 20% and repeat.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Reload 17841, drop the plasma current to 410 kA.
postshot_description: OK, but density too low.

preshot_description: Increased density by 30%.
postshot_description: OK. Density still low.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Ok. Density slightly higher.

preshot_description: Restore 15724 and add NBI.
postshot_description: Forgot to select NBI in MCS panel.

preshot_description: Repeat with beam selected.
postshot_description: Shot terminates at 350 ms, beam OK.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: OK, termination at 340 ms as before.

preshot_description: i/b gas set to 944+60 (leak now fixed)
postshot_description: fair: density about 15% higher than 17074, 1st sawtooth slightly earlier, flux consumption somewhat higher (could be density). No H mode until Vloop goes to zero.  Ruby TS no data.

preshot_description: Restore 17815. SS beam from 0.050, 1.7MW. feedback density control, no i/b helios input.
postshot_description: Pretty good. Shot went into H mode at the time when reference disrupted, then went a bit chaotic - waveforms need tidying. Density well below reference despite gas valves wide open. Efit failed. target probes say strike point is about 40mm too far in at 0.120, less later. Ruby TS OK.

preshot_description: raise Idiv by 2ka at 0.120m 0.5kA at 0.200 - may give vertical control problem. Extend vloop w/f.
postshot_description: Hm. No beam. FBIS trip. Enable from PCS is OK. Efit OK. Strike point always > 1m so no use. (why is ALP in mm??)

preshot_description: try again.
postshot_description: Beam! Large plasma event instead of H mode this time (probably sawtooth), never mind - measurement phase looks OK. According to ALP the strike point is smack on target from 0.110 to 0.230s. No tin lines seen - this is bad. No ESM data (for strike point radius). Upper and lower peak Jsats similar. No ATM data.

preshot_description: Try again, increase spectrometer integration time.
postshot_description: OK beam and shot. this time disrupted at 0.320. Strike points OK - ESM and ALP agree (ish). Still no tin.

preshot_description: Try to scan strike point radius.
postshot_description: Good, swept strike point from 0.940 to 1.050m (ALP measurement). Still no tin seen.

preshot_description: restore 17850, including NBI settings.
postshot_description: OK shot. density about 20% higher than reference, effect of wall loading + flow control.

preshot_description: repeat with probe.
postshot_description: plasma OK. probe a little outside LCFS.

preshot_description: repeat, inserting RP 5mm further.
postshot_description: OK shot and beam.

preshot_description: rerun, probe in a bit further.
postshot_description: looks fine.

preshot_description: adjust IDIV to lift off CC. Retract probe a bit.
postshot_description: not a bad guess - plasma makes just glancing contact with CC from about 150-250ms

preshot_description: realise that the previous shots were using optical feedback. Tweaks in IDIV were actually compensating radial changes due to non-flat DRREF. Switch to magnetic feedback and straighten up but increase IDIV. Lower DRREF flattop in anticipation of offset
postshot_description: rather wobbly handover, probably due to increased coupling of Ip feedback to Bv.

preshot_description: Use PF results of 17864 to set physics waveforms. Move DRREF to counter the offset. Set a very gradual handover from feed-forward to feedback control
postshot_description: Ramp-up is better behaved and there is less overshoot in Ip, but flattop is showing some oscillation

preshot_description: Change control parameters to reduce cross-coupling of feedback and use longer Bv control and Ip integral time constants.
postshot_description: A much better behaved shot. Some slight CC interaction and outer radius is a bit low and drifts up to original position by 330ms, but no control oscillations.

preshot_description: Insert RP and repeat
postshot_description: good shot

preshot_description: repeat with RP 1cm further in
postshot_description: ohmic shot - no disruption. Looks like resulting radius was different too

preshot_description: switch to ohmic shots. Reload 15727 and push Zref down by 5cm
postshot_description: good, looks like SOL flow changed to mostly lower x-point as required

preshot_description: repeat with RP moved in
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: repeat with RP moved again
postshot_description: looks good

preshot_description: reload 17815, push Zref up 10cm to get beam-heated USND L-mode. 1.8MW NBI from 50ms, start shot with NBI already in sync.
postshot_description: disrupted due to FA trip during ramp-up at 115ms

preshot_description: reduce Zref and ZDgain and increase ZPgain
postshot_description: no better. FA2 gave out at 102ms and FA1 followed at 108ms

preshot_description: revert to normal Z gain. Delay pushing Zref up until plasma is fully formed.
postshot_description: Got a full length plasma, but still no sign of tin. Strike point is a bit inboard of where we want it

preshot_description: reload standard shot - DIp probe is inserted in upper divertor
postshot_description: Good shot - real time density failed

preshot_description: set beam start time dfor SW and SS at 100 ms - keep fuelling on till the end of the shot (previously cut off at 200 ms )
postshot_description: NO SS beam-FBIS trip - no real time density-large event at 300 ms - density under dense from 60 ms

preshot_description: increase flow rate to 18 from 15 in period 40 to 100 ms - bring start of inboard to 60 ms
postshot_description: no beam again from SS - no FBIS - better density match

preshot_description: reload  shot 17873 for Seb while waiting for the beams - with RP recip - DIP probe still in
postshot_description: didn't get the reciprocation as forgot to load the waveform

preshot_description: added HFS mid-plane gas puff at 1 bar - hope to get both beams
postshot_description: No SS again - good SW and good high density

preshot_description: Retry
Restore 17815: Sneak in a pulse for Adam. No Beams
postshot_description: Strike point not in the right place - No useful information, shot needs beams

preshot_description: Restore 17886: Add Gas 5, He puff 2ms at t=320. Select IBgas. Reduce Zref by 0.1.
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: increase IB pressure to 2.5 bar, move He puff to 0.33
postshot_description: one beam, it withstands such high density with decreasing current

preshot_description: move IB gas 60 ms later
postshot_description: nice shot

preshot_description: reload 16479 and increase He puff to 2 ms

preshot_description: Try again again

Good ELM-free H-mode from 220 with consequent sharp rise in density following.
Disrupts at 320 ms though.
The ELMs obviously aren't in a mood to appear in order to be mitigated today.

Zero EF0208.

Beams both fired.
Not very ELMy.

preshot_description: standard shot

preshot_description: restore 17683, plus EFC settings from 17928. Zero EFC/0511. SS from 0.095s, SW from 0.170s.
postshot_description: Ooops - good beams and good high density H mode, BUT, I left the HFS gas on. (using density feedback, so all other gas shut off). Interestingly, the LF mode accelerates throughout.  Several ELMs. Lose H mode at 0.340.

preshot_description: retry. set Omaha to 1MHz from t=0
postshot_description:
good beams again. more elm-free-ish and terminated completely when previous shot lost H mode.  Gas shuts off about 0.170 except for blip after event at 0.200. Mode faster at 0.250 than previous, then slowing, but still rotating at 5.5kHz at termination.
betaN >4 for 0.060s.

preshot_description: repeat with both EFC zeroed.
postshot_description: Earlier H mode, then killed by IRE at 0.200, shot lived on at high Vloop. It's a good job we bought these EFCCs!

preshot_description: repeat with both EFC as standard
postshot_description: Hm, the mystery deepens. Early H mode again, lost just before 0.300s.

preshot_description: reload 17930 EFC settings. Run at TF=0.5.
postshot_description: SS a bit late starting and SW short, but short had bad event at 0.220 probably not caused by late SS. Only 0.300 long. Mode starts a little later, but betaP is a little lower also, wrt 17933.

preshot_description: repeat at TF=0.45
postshot_description: beams OK this time. bad event comes earlier - 0.120 and shot very sick thereafter.

postshot_description: SS cut out at 0.200. Brief H mode from 0.220, but still disrupted at 0.360 despite lack of H mode. leaves c/c at 0.080. Density quite a bit lower, gas running flat-out until 0.230. Zebra PC failed.

preshot_description: rerun for full beam, adjusting early Vloop and Idiv slightly.

preshot_description: rerun with 2stage Ip ramp.

preshot_description:

zero EF0511

postshot_description: Ace beams. Control improved, still wibbling around a bit 0.070-0.120, but didnt hit anything. H mode a little intermittent and LF mode weaker.

Density failed to jump up at 0.150, the combined LFS midplane and t/b are not a match for the old midplane. nb we also have 20ms prefill at 4V instead of 9ms at 5V, despite which the initial density is still low, tho the plasma is small too (cf ADA)

postshot_description: 2 good beams. Density now matches 8855 well, but still no H mode.

preshot_description: restore 18342 (H mode long inter-elms)
postshot_description: short SW pulse, H mode but more ELMy than 18342. Disrupts much the same time (0.320). TM starts later but reaches much the same amplitude.

preshot_description: NSTX-like setup. Slow Ip ramp to 3.2MA/s (ramp ends 0.165(0.110)), slow all other waveforms, Bv, density, Rout, etc. Early beams.
postshot_description: On c/c till 0.150 then grazing. H mode onset about same time but ELMy. core SX higher. TM shows up earlier (0.250) when betap is higher, then slows to a halt causing density collapse. li not measureably different.

preshot_description: go for earlier diversion - revert to rout from 18367 and raise idiv 5KA. Drop P3 to 3KV(3.3).
postshot_description:
patchy beam, mostly about 2MW. Earlier and stronger H mode, TM delayed by 50ms.
Early SX reduced. li reduced (tho beta comes up later) Rout grows more slowly pre 0.080s. fs~2.0.

preshot_description: retry for full beams. Tune Ip and Vloop to match actual.
postshot_description: 2 good beams. Goes ELM-free almost immediately. RT Hene fringe hop at 0.250 (dont understand these). SXR buildup - seems to be carbon. li plateaus at 0.8 - not fantastic but better. betaN just hits 4. fs falling to 1.6.  FAs working hard.

preshot_description: delay SW NBI until start of flattop. RP in use.
postshot_description: almost no change. FAs survive terminal event at 0.288

preshot_description: change NBI timing
postshot_description: brief earlier H mode, then ELMing - strangely. Lasted a bit longer (0.320), tho' final beta is reduced. Much less broad profile (li and SX).

preshot_description: Revert to early NBI and accelerate density ramp (requires LFS)
postshot_description: HSV goes mad. Disruption replaced by IRE which the plasma survives and goes on into ELM-free to hit betaN=5. I think it's q0=2 which has been hitting these shots.

preshot_description: raise density plateau factor 1.5
postshot_description: brief interruption to PINI, otherwise OK. Plasma similar but IRE delayed, Vloop never recovers. H mode not earlier and immediately ELM free. Hmode does come back.

preshot_description: Revert to slow density ramp, like 18372 but stretched 100ms.  Shorten prefill 5ms.
postshot_description: generally well behaved until the 0.420 (sawtooth?). Very late and weak H mode.

preshot_description: do it again with HFS only.
postshot_description: A little better - there is a preprogrammed Ip rampdown.

postshot_description: OK

OV and OVI signals up >50% around 0.100s. He about the same.

postshot_description: Spotted something troubling that's been going on all day  - EFIT says that the plasma is at Z_0 = +10 cm, moving upwards from midplane at 100 ms. D-alpha bears this out, as does the B&W camera. TAE coils are not turned on. Very bizarre, and there is no point continuing with the high beta campaign while this is unresolved.

betaN slightly>4. (li(2)~0.87)

preshot_description: Restored standard plasma shot 21308.
postshot_description: OK.

postshot_description: OK.

postshot_description: Shot, impurity gas and TAE drive OK.

postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Restored TAE shot 18487.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Repeat with TAE sweep changes.
postshot_description: OK. Hard xray warning.

preshot_description: Repeat, with inboard helios fuelling active.

postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Repeat previous shot with TS valve open.
postshot_description: OK.

postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Repeat last shot to see whether we can go lower in density.
postshot_description: OK. No IRE this time, density is slightly lower and definitely more stationary. Pulse ends at 335 ms.

preshot_description: Increase density to 2.5 10^19 m-3.
postshot_description: OK. But density too high.

preshot_description: Increase plasma current to 800 kA.
postshot_description: Density feed-back didn't work.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: IRE at 193 ms after which we lost control of the density and run out of flux.

preshot_description: Standard shot.
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description:
Repeat 20901 (SND, close to lower TAE-coils).
SS NBI: start 0.120s, duration 0.080s, voltage 62kV
Omaha: 2MHz, start -0.01s,  duration 0.5s, on same time base as TAE.
postshot_description: Density rises due to inboard Helios. Switch Helios off for the next shot.

preshot_description:
Repeat. DRREF changed to increase outer radius to 1.5m.
Outboard Helios impurity puffs included for T. Morgan
postshot_description: OK. outer R reaches 1.5m at 0.120ms but drops to 1.45m.

preshot_description:
Increased shape from 0.65 to 0.75.
IDIV lowered slightly in between 0.100s and 0.250s.
Outboard Helios puffs shifted 110ms forwards.
postshot_description: OK. X -point still moving.

preshot_description:
Try to make a centre column limited SND:
* IDIV lowered further. P2 reversal enabled.
* Outer radius to 1.55m.
postshot_description:
Plasma just limited by the centre column and slightly touching the GDC plate.
This confuses the D-alpha boundary determination in EFIT. So we might want to reduce the outer radius again.

preshot_description:
Tom Morgan has got all his data: outboard Helios switched off.
Reduced outer R back to 1.50m.
IDIV even lower (by 0.1kA) to get a more limited plasma.
Increase plasma current (from 600kA to 700kA) and decrease TF (from -0.55T to -0.5T) to lower q95.
postshot_description:
Plasma current trace a bit bumpy.
GDC plate glowing even more. TAE coils also touched by the plasma.
We need to reduce the DRREF further.

preshot_description:
DRREF reduced by another 3cm.
Visual feedback switch over to magnetic feedback.
postshot_description: Outer radius now OK. 2 events at 0.160s and at 0.174s.

preshot_description: Abandoning the limited plasmas. Repeat #21647. Shift it down by 3cm and decrease the shaping from 0.65 to 0.55.
postshot_description: Plasma OK, but too small and too far away from the TAE coils.

preshot_description: Increased the outer radius to 1.5m. Increase IDIV up to 15kA. Decreased BV by 0.04T.
postshot_description: Not a very good shot. Plasma moves outwards until it hits the TAE coils (in other words it's too close now).

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Plasma this time, but not a very good one: too big and unstable.

preshot_description:
Repeat.
Prefill even earlier (at -0.02).
postshot_description: Good shot!

preshot_description:
Repeat.
TF reduced from 0.5T to 0.4T.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description:
Repeat.
TF increased to 0.585T.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Standard plasma shot.
postshot_description: Ran OK but much shorter than usual. Density far too high in spite of density feedback because real-time density went wrong (unplugged cable on CO2 system).

preshot_description: Restore 21651. Change from density feedback to flow ref to avoid problem with CO2, trying to match (roughly) reference waveforms. Switch radial feedback to magnetics (changing gain parameters). Set SS NBI from 100 to 200ms.
postshot_description: Good shot (surprisingly). 2 breakdowns before beam start.

preshot_description: Repeat. Reduce outer radius reference by 30cm. Switch off inboard Helios.
postshot_description: OK. Good beams. Density lower due to inboard Helios off. Plasma radius about 20cm smaller.

preshot_description: Repeat. (with lower TAE antenna frequency)
postshot_description: Good shot. Good beams.

preshot_description: Retry.
postshot_description: Ran OK. Early disruption due to arcing on centre column.

preshot_description: Reload 21294. Add 1.5kAt of EFCCs 02&08.
postshot_description: Density is larger than in 21294. No pump-out observed. Plasma is now too high vertically compared to 21294 (magnetic axis is higher by ~2cm).

preshot_description:
Repeat.
 Reference => 21689.
postshot_description: Shot OK but maybe not enough light from helium.

preshot_description: Increase Ip to 750kA, hoping to get more light from helium.
postshot_description: OK, maybe more light.

preshot_description: Standard shot.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description:
Reload 21683.
 Reference => 21683.
postshot_description: Shot OK. Problem with interferometry density measurement but it should be transient and we have YAG data anyway.

preshot_description:
Repeat with ELM coils waveforms from 21292.

postshot_description: ELM PSUs C and D didn't fire. No pump-out observed.

preshot_description:
Repeat.
 Reference => 21683.
postshot_description: Only PSU C failed. Still no sign of pump-out.

preshot_description:
Repeat but put 200A in the coils from the beginning of the shot for test purposes.
 Reference => 21683.
postshot_description: PSU C still didn't work...

preshot_description:
Try again.
 Reference => 21683.
postshot_description: PSUs B and C failed.

preshot_description:
Repeat again.
 Reference => 21683.
postshot_description: A and C failed!?!

preshot_description:
Restore 21687: Effect of Error field coils.

postshot_description: Pump out seen at 330ms. Looks like a standard locked mode.

preshot_description: Increase flow ref to 5e21. Select Gas group 11 & 12 (and PV9).

preshot_description: Repeat with the standard EFCCs settings for reference.
postshot_description: OK. Very similar to previous shot.

preshot_description: Add 2kA in both EFCCs.
postshot_description: Still no pump-out.

preshot_description: Repeat 21703 with a reciprocation of the probe.
postshot_description: No interferometry density signal. YAG density shows no sign of pump-out. Plasma disrupts at 400ms.

preshot_description: The same but with the probe a bit less far inside the plasma. Add ELM coils blip after 500ms for test purposes.
postshot_description: Pump-out seen again! All the ELM coils worked.

preshot_description: Reload high density shot 21704 and add probe reciprocation.
postshot_description: Good shot. All ELm coils worked again.

preshot_description: Again
postshot_description: Good shot. Pump-out observed.

preshot_description: Repeat but turn off ELM coils and do a probe reciprocation.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Repeat with ELM coils on and a probe reciprocation.
postshot_description: good data - pump out seen but not as large as in 21711

preshot_description: Reduce IELM to 1 kA - keep RP reciprocation
postshot_description: No interferometry density again. From YAG data, no pump-out appears.

preshot_description: Restore 21346 (scenario 2).
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat with ELM coils.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Repeat with probe reciprocation.

ELM coils worked fine.

repeat.

OK.
Z-position not low enough.

repeat 21708 (scenario 1).

repeat.
switch on ELM coils from 0.33s for 0.1s at 0.7kA.

no beams. camera_ok stayed on but lost control at 0.240 - no clear why

Some loss of Z control at end of Ip ramp - not clear if this is the cause of problem.  Ip overshot slightly - could have reduced Vloop. No cameras functional to help.

preshot_description: Match IPREF better to measured Ip to get a better handover, reduce early BV to get a larger plasma.

preshot_description: Match early BV phase better to allow better handover
postshot_description: IRE ends in VDE at 0.15s, start-up is worse than before, beams good though

preshot_description: Halve EFCCs current (1kA).

preshot_description: Standard shot, modified to use ECC for error field correction.

postshot_description: Good shot - lokks liek these are better settings.  Density a bit wavey - out of the LFS valves only w/f 3 is in use.

preshot_description: Reduce ramp rate some more, raise gas during ramp, and adjust ECC currents
postshot_description: No SS beam (operator didnt hear start of shot) Better but still dropping density at 0.240. plasma going over-sized about 0.120s

preshot_description: retry
postshot_description: Disaster.  Homer locked onto beam dump and plasma inflated.

postshot_description: Shot and beams basically ran OK but still IRE/event at 0.230s, hence rather short flattop. Radial control pretty poor, but Homer agrees with ADA.

postshot_description: Good beams and shot. Disrupt at 0.360, probably sawtooth. Density ramping up all 4 ECC OK.

preshot_description: Throttle back on gas during flattop, otherwise no change
postshot_description: No SW beam, disrupt at 0.260 - density only slightly reduced at that time

postshot_description: Good shot. Though would have liked the density to be lower.

postshot_description: Good shot. IRE/VDE at 360ms.
