preshot_description:
Reload 22099 w/ gas from today. Add GAS8 at full from 0-200 ms.

Having problems with PCS - spurious errors (P1 fatal error from nowhere that fixed on logout and also 21935 gas reload is different now from earlier!)
postshot_description: Whoops. Evidently a different shot was reloaded while GMcA was diagnosing PCS in my absence.

preshot_description: Try again
postshot_description: IRE @ 200 ms

preshot_description:
Add ELM coil waveforms from 22328.
Increase IB gas to 2B.
postshot_description: Good shot

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description:
OK, we're back in business.  No H-mode though.
But that's the end of the morning session.

preshot_description: Restore shot 22315. Reduce FLOW_REF by 30%.
postshot_description: Good shot, but SW NBI has notch.

preshot_description: Repeat, hoping for good SW NBI.
postshot_description: Good shot and NBI.

preshot_description: Repeat, with EFCC waveforms from 22316.
postshot_description: Good shot. SS started a little late.

preshot_description: Repeat. PF parameters found to be wrongly set for optical plasma radius control. Corrected.
postshot_description:
Good shot and NBI. Improved radial control. FA3 tripped at shot start, affecting
EF correction.

preshot_description: Repeat, hoping for proper EFCC behaviour.
postshot_description: Good shot, but FA3 tripped again at shot start. This is a problem for the programme.

preshot_description: Repeat after abort.
postshot_description: Shot terminated early. FA3 failed again.

preshot_description: Because of FA3 problem, restore shot 22264. Reverse EFCC polarity and increase current.
postshot_description: Good shot and NBI. Strong plasma interaction with RP inserted for test.

preshot_description: Repeat without RP. FA3 disabled in MCS Parameters because of FA3 failure.
postshot_description: Shot ok, but several NBI breakdowns.

preshot_description: restore standard shot with modified EFC and ELM coil settings (EFC in n=2, ELM coils for error correction) , disable FA3
postshot_description: good repeat, however disrupts at 0.267s

preshot_description: Restore 17176. Alter MCS parameters for counter operation (Ip dirn and P2 reversing). Reverse Vloop, Idiv and Ip waveforms. Deselect FA4 and SCS4 and zero EF waveforms. Increase EFPS time window to get rid of PCS error message.
postshot_description: Good shot (surprisingly...). Only 50ms shorter than reference.

preshot_description: Repeat. Increase prefill by 50%. Enable the ELM coils.
postshot_description: Ran OK. Plasma much shorter than previous one. Strong vertical oscillation of the plasma. It was already the case in shot 22376 but wasn't noticed...

preshot_description: Repeat. Decrease divertor current by 5kA. Re-enable FA4 and SCS4, reload EFCC waveforms from 22375 and change EF control gain time from 10ms to 100ms for test purpose.
postshot_description: Nice shot. Changing the gain did improve the situation for EFC0208 drive but it is far from being perfect...

preshot_description: Reload the daily standard shot 22288. Change MCS parameters for counter operation and reverse Ip and PF waveforms. Deselect SS beam.
postshot_description: Good shot. The plasma once again goes through a strong vertical oscillations phase, but it stabilizes after 200ms. Apart from that, extremely similar to reference.

preshot_description: Reload 22297 (beam heated). Change MCS parameters for counter operation and reverse Ip and PF waveforms. Deselect FA3 and FA4. Restore EF settings from 22379. Zero EF0511 waveform. Increase amplitude of EF0208 to 500A and change the gain time constant to 50ms.
postshot_description: Disruption at 200ms. Probably linked to loss of vertical control (strong oscillations phase once again before the disruption).

preshot_description: Repeat. Change ZP gain down to 0.1 and ZD gain up to 0.6. Increase EF gain time constant to 250ms.
postshot_description: Disrupts even earlier. The amplitude of the oscillations had decreased before the disruption but the FAs tripped. SCS4 blipped with an overshoot.

preshot_description: Repeat. Change EF gain time constant to 1000ms. Switch vertical position control to analogue.
postshot_description: Not better.

preshot_description: Repeat again.
postshot_description: Ok. Shot longer than reference. Still some oscillations visible towards the end of the shot after the vertical position ramp.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: No oscillation on the vertical feedback. Shot marginally better than reference, but vertical control is lost after 200 ms. There is no current in the EF coils and FA4 is not selected.

preshot_description: Enabled FA4 and changes polarity of EF coils.
postshot_description: Shot lasts longer, but still nicely oscillating up and down. Terminates at 300 ms.

preshot_description: Changed the start time of SCS4 to 4.9 s instead of 5 s and kept IDIV constant after 220 ms.
postshot_description: Bad shot also because the duration of the SCS4 enable window was too short.

preshot_description: Increased duration of SCS4 window from 100 ms to 250 ms. Dropped ZD gain from 1.0 to 0.2.
postshot_description: Ok. Longer plasma, looks vertically more stable (no oscillations).

preshot_description: Increased the duration of SCS4 window to 500 ms.
postshot_description: Low frequency mode appears at 250 ms.

preshot_description: Switched off SCS4 and FA4.
postshot_description: n=1 mode appears again.

preshot_description: Increased current in the ELM coils by 30%.
postshot_description: Mode is not there, but we only got one beam.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Ok.

preshot_description: Enable SCS4 from 5 s for 0.5 s and drive EF coils from 250 ms to 550 ms.
postshot_description: Shot terminates at 300 ms.

preshot_description: Changed EF coils waveforms, enabled FA4. No beams.
postshot_description: Ok. Very short flat top.

preshot_description: retry
postshot_description: Good. Shot ran fine.

preshot_description: Restore 22297, apply counter changes. drop ZD gain to 0.2 (HSCU missing) and change PF plasma coupling to suit optical radial control. ELM coils 0.6/0.3KA. EFCC zero. SS NBI from 0.1, SW from 0.2. Gas under flowref control.
postshot_description: Excellent, tho a bit high on density.

preshot_description: Standard plasma shot (restore 22406)
postshot_description: Good repeat

preshot_description: Restore yesterday's final shot, 22408. Reduce gas to bring density down.
postshot_description: Died early, also some SS breakdown. Density still higher than reference.

preshot_description:
Reload impurity gas from 22327 (outboard Helios - He from 0.200).
Reduce flowref sustain level from 3 to 2.5.
postshot_description: Didn't make much difference to density. Still falls over at same time as previous shot - locked mode.

preshot_description: Reduce flowref to 1. restore EFCC from 22313 and flip sign.
postshot_description: Still early disruption

preshot_description:
Flip EFCC sign.
ELM coils zeroed from 230 ms.
postshot_description:
Density is a bit closer, but still that early disruption persists.
SW didn't fire.

preshot_description:
Restore ELM coils from 22416.
Zero EF.
Increase gas by 30%.
postshot_description: Same

preshot_description: Beams 50 ms earlier
postshot_description: Long shot, huge density

preshot_description:
Remove He puffing after 300 ms.
Add EF from 22305.
postshot_description: FA 2 tripped at 225 ms for no obvious cause.

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: Good shot

preshot_description: Decrease EFCC flat-top from 5 to 3
postshot_description: 1 beam only. Otherwise OK.

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: FA trip

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: 1 beam.

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Reduce gas flow by 33%
postshot_description: Disruption at 0.2

preshot_description: Restore 22223, change polarity.
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: Lock mode at 0.25.

preshot_description: Delay beams by 50 ms.
postshot_description: Second beam effectively kills it.

preshot_description: Load outboard Helios waveform from 22419 and shift it 100 ms earlier.
postshot_description: Disruption at 0.25.

preshot_description: Move beams 50 ms later.
postshot_description: Start wobbling at 0.22. IB puff is back.

preshot_description: Repeat. Remove outboard Helios waveform.
postshot_description: SS beam starts 50 ms later.

preshot_description: Move beams 50 ms earlier.
postshot_description: SS beam is later.

preshot_description: Move beams earlier.
postshot_description: No SS beam.

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: Both beams are in time;  shot dies at 0.16.

preshot_description: Move beams later.
postshot_description: No SS beam.

preshot_description: Move beams later.
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Increase pressure to 2.6; change beam time.
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Reduce IB pressure to 0.9.
postshot_description: No IB puff at all; disruption at 0.23.

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: IB gas is back. SW is shorter, and SS is later.

preshot_description: Switch off IB puff, change beam time.
postshot_description: Too low density.

preshot_description: Switch gas on; reduce beam power.
postshot_description: No IB gas.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: No gas.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Gas is back.

preshot_description: Boronisation recovery.  Restore 22376, import gas from 20059 and switch polarity.  Extend prefill to 15ms.
postshot_description: First plasma of the day!

preshot_description:
Tested the inboard helios before the shot.Stop trying boronisation recovery shots and switch to the main programme.
Repeat 22122:
* modified for counter injection.
* IPREF and IDIV modified to 800kA ( i.e. times 0.9)
* Inboard Helios.
* SS NBI: start 0.05s, duration 0.40s, voltage 66kV
* SW NBI: start 0.10s, duration 0.25s, voltage 60kV
* FA3 deselected.
* Thomson times changed.
postshot_description:
Beams OK.
Disruption at 0.200s.
Inboard helios didn't trigger: so most probably too low density.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description:
Good plasma.
SW NBI is a bit short (only 0.09s).
Plasma position seems a bit too high.

preshot_description:
Repeat.
Thomson times changed.
Inboard Helios tested.
postshot_description:
Inboard gas puff works, but disruption at 0.230s.
FA trips, VDE.

preshot_description:
Repeat.
* Reload Outboard Helios impurity puff from 22419 (shift by 50ms).
* Outboard helios nozzle to 830mm.
* Changed Thomson times.
* Outboard helios (impurity) and inboard helios tested intershot (  2 tries, 1 worked).
postshot_description:
No beam!
Inboard Helios did work.
VDE at 0.150s.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: OK. Good shot

preshot_description:
Repeat.
* TC5 (PV1), HL1(PV3) and HU8 (PV3) off, all others on. 
* Now modulating GAS1 and GAS3 and GAS 11.
* Compensating with the rest.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description:
Repeat.
* HL1(PV3) and HU6 (PV3) off, all others on.
* Now modulating GAS2 and GAS3 and GAS 12.
* Compensating with the rest.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Restore standard counter plasma shot (22406).
postshot_description: Good shot.

preshot_description: Restore 21773. Convert to counter operation. Deselect FA3 and zero EFCC0208 waveform. Set Zref to 0. Zero ELM coils current. Ruby time set to 0.4s and XLP time to 0.2s.
postshot_description: Shorter than reference shot with much lower density. The EFCCs haven't been reversed so error field correction wasn't good in this shot.

preshot_description: Repeat. SW deselected (still conditionning).
postshot_description: OK, shot went through. SS had 1 breakdown. Plasma underdense and short. No H-mode.

preshot_description: Increase flow ref by 30% after t=0. Add SW beam at 150ms.
postshot_description: Good shot. Very large density. H-mode from 260 to 360ms. One of the P5 coils illuminated (visible light!) by the plasma.

preshot_description: Move beams 50ms earlier. Ruby TS set at 0.3s.
postshot_description: Good shot. SS beam OK. SW lost from 130 to 370ms. Nice H-mode with big ELMs. The ELMs are interestingly grouped by bursts of 2 or 3.

preshot_description: Repeat. Deselect SW (experiencing problems). Set ELM coils current to 1.4kA between 0.3 and 0.4s.
postshot_description: Good shot. More ELMs with still that bursty behaviour.

preshot_description: Repeat without the ELM coils.
postshot_description: Identical to last shot until NBI drops out at 0.320.

preshot_description: repeat for full beam
postshot_description: NBI dropped out at 0.300. Density only recovered due to automatic rampdown gas flood. Early density slightly lower than 22472 (lack of wall loading?)

preshot_description: repeat for full beam
postshot_description: good beam and plasma. Very very similar to 22472.

preshot_description: repeat with SW from 0.100s
postshot_description: Good beams and shot - seriously high density. 2 largeish ELMS and a string of smaller ones.

preshot_description: repeat with 1.4KA in all ELM coils from 0.3s
postshot_description: Good beams and shot. Microscopically different from last shot. SS started at t=0.

preshot_description:
restore SND shot 21924. Raise flow ref factor 1.3. SS from 0.070, SW from 0.100
Zref to +0.20m
postshot_description: Short shot. 10kHz mode slows and locks.

preshot_description: Switch to NTV programme. restore 22419, EF from 22476, ELM coils at 1.4KA.
postshot_description: SS started 50ms late.  Terminated at 0.320. nb this shot is not very different from 22477 apart from lower delta, slightly higher Ip and lower density.

preshot_description: repeat for full beam, and raise gas input 5%
postshot_description: SS started at 0.0709. Shot pretty much identical with 22479, density very slightly higher but still below reference

preshot_description: one more go, raise gas flow by 2 throughout.
postshot_description: SS 50ms late again but shot ran through. ELM A cut out (didnt reset by hand before shot).  density only microscopically higher than 22480. Mode still present but faded away.

preshot_description: one more go, delay EFC start to 0.270
postshot_description: Good beams and disrupt at 0.320 again with strong mode. All ELM coils fired but not long before termination. Density on the high side.

preshot_description: Try again with fingers crossed
postshot_description: Good beams and full length shot. Again mode died away. All 4 ELM coils OK.

preshot_description: restore 22465 (counter, flow and magnetic control. raise flow 20%, invert EFC, reduce Rout 5cm after 0.25s. w/f 9 waveform from
postshot_description: Good shot. Helios puffs visible on both cameras. Plasma size looks OK, density maybe a little high.

preshot_description: Restore ELM waveforms from 21774 (1.4KA each from 0.300s).
postshot_description: Density lower but even before coils come on. Vloop somewhat higher too.  4 ELM coils OK.

preshot_description: repeat with Rout reduced by 0.100m
postshot_description: ELM coil A failed despite not showing yellow before 'prepare' . Radius improved. density rising after 0.400

preshot_description: repeat after manually resetting ELM PSUs
postshot_description: All EFC OK. Density dipped 0.180-0.200 but recovered by 0.250. Pumpout observed thereafter. Distinct MHD visible on AMA during this time as well as after 0.350

preshot_description: repeat with zero ELM currents.
postshot_description: OK - density rising (phew)

preshot_description: Repeat 22487 at ECC=1KA. Manual reset ELM PSUs.
postshot_description: OK shot rising density, but still mode 0.2-0.3s. No mode evident during ELM activation.

preshot_description: repeat at 1.2KA
postshot_description: 4 ECC OK. Density a bit low from the start.

preshot_description: Increase gas input to 5(4) - had to invoke group 1 as well as 2. ZERO ECC currents.
postshot_description: little effect on early density, rising later as normal for ECC=0. No MHD.

preshot_description: Try harder to push up early density.
postshot_description: Density started ramping up faster but then got dragged down by mode from 0.2-0.300s.  But - carried on rising after 0.300s. Density still well below 21773 despite quite a bit more gas input.

preshot_description: Revert to 1.4KA ECC current but shorter pulse - to observe decay of ER after coils come off.
postshot_description: Premature disruption at 0.450. ELM A cut out at peak current - maybe creating n=1 error exaggerating locked mode behaviour. Early density tracks shot 92.

preshot_description: Try again
postshot_description: Looks OK. Highish early density then ramps down, full length.

preshot_description: Standard plasma shot for counter operation.
postshot_description: Ok. Good plasma, identical to reference.

preshot_description: Restore shot 22476 (top/bottom fuelled 2-beam H-mode scenario).
postshot_description: Ok. SW PINI tripped at about 350 ms. As for the rest similar to reference shot.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Ok, decent shot, slightly underdense with respect to reference.

preshot_description: Reduced outer radius by further 2 cm and moved the step down in plasma outer radius earlier by 40 ms.
postshot_description: Ok, density still slightly lower than in reference shot.

preshot_description: Reload fuelling waveform from 21568.
postshot_description: Density too low, IRE at 200 ms, lost H-mode.

preshot_description: Cut off fuelling after 200 ms.
postshot_description: Ok. Got the H-mode back.

preshot_description: Repeat previous shot with two beams. Add some helium for radial electric field measurement.
postshot_description: SW beam trips at 200 ms IRE at 250 ms and eventually runs out of flux at 330 ms. We still get the H-mode at about 230 ms.

preshot_description: Repeat, Helios gas waveform starts at 200 ms.
postshot_description: Good shot, but SW beam is about 200 ms late.

preshot_description: Repeat. SW beam from 150 ms instead of 100 ms.
postshot_description: Good shot and NBI.

preshot_description: Repeat, with FLOW_REF cutoff 20ms earlier.
postshot_description: Shot and NBI OK, but IRE at 250ms because of FLOW_REF change.

preshot_description: Repeat, extending fuelling 10ms. Prevent gas blowout which affects following shot by reducing IPGAIN to 0.85.
postshot_description: Excellent 0.5s shot and NBI, with widely space ELMs. Blowout prevented.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Another good shot and NBI. Density a little lower than previous shot.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Disrupted at 280ms. SS NBI late.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Same early disruption. This time SS NBI fired ok.

preshot_description: Repeat, with SW NBI start at 220ms.
postshot_description: Disruption now slightly later.

preshot_description: Repeat, with gas category from shot 21568, increasing last section of FLOW_REF by 20%.
postshot_description: Disrupted early again. SS NBI late. Low density.

preshot_description: Repeat. Restore impurity gas waveforms from 22512 (overwritten in error in previous shot setup). Increase and extend last section of FLOW_REF waveform.
postshot_description: Better.

preshot_description: Standard plasma shot for counter operation.
postshot_description: Ok.

preshot_description: Straight repeat of 22509. ELM coils in configuration 12. Late inboard midplane gas puff disabled.
postshot_description: Disrupts early because of a locked mode.

preshot_description: Repeat. Ruby time back to 330 ms.
postshot_description: Longer shot, killed by an IRE shortly before 300 ms. Lost one of the ELM coils power supplies (D).

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Disrupts early again.

preshot_description: Doubled the current in the ELM coils.
postshot_description: Longer shot. No SS PINI.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: SS PINI late. Disrupts at the same time as the previous shot. Lost ELM coil A.

preshot_description: Reverted to EFCC. Reduced Ip and IDIV by a factor 0.9.
postshot_description: Longer shot but IRE reappears shortly before 300 ms.

preshot_description: Increased Ip and IDIV.
postshot_description: Disrupts slightly earlier.

preshot_description: Prolonged gas puff by 20 ms. Added two puffs from GAS9 at 200 ms and 250 ms.
postshot_description: Ok. Shot dies because runs out of flux. Otherwise fine. Rather puzzling...

preshot_description: Repeat. Added more puffs on GAS9.
postshot_description: Good repeat. SW PINI breaks down at 100 ms but comes back later.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: SS PINI about 50 ms late. Otherwise good shot.

preshot_description: 22524 (650 kA shot) + gas from 22528
postshot_description: Lasts longer than reference.

preshot_description: 22527 with 2x faster current ramp, and only to 700 kA
postshot_description: Ip ramp is in two parts

preshot_description: Adjust early Vloop
postshot_description: Didn't really help

preshot_description:
Slow Ip ramp to finish at 130 ms.
Add OB Helios spike at 150 ms.
GC: Add IB Helios @ 1 s to test.
postshot_description: Still not a particularly useful shot - big IRE @ 250 ms. i/b helios OK.

preshot_description: Restore 22477 (higher density H mode shot - abandon NBCD expt. and switch to sawtooth control)
postshot_description: SS didn't fire. i/b Helios failed

preshot_description: Try again, ZERo and disable ELM coils.
postshot_description: OK shot, high density. TMPs tripped. i/b Helios OK.

preshot_description: Disable i/b Helios test to avoid TMP trips. Set Zref=+10cm, retract Helios probe 2cm
postshot_description: TMPs tripped again despite no Helios.  Major IRE at 0.200, brief precursor mode at 7kHz. Density matches 22534.

preshot_description: Switch to Zref =-10cm. Reload Helios gas from 22531 and enable grp. 7.
postshot_description: No SS beam (trigger not received). IRE again nevertheless.

preshot_description: retry
postshot_description:
Density a little higher than 22535 and failed to ramp down completely, otherwise OK. 
One eared Ruby TS density profile (seeing Helios ???)

preshot_description: Standard shot for reversed Ip
postshot_description:
Good 
No colour camera for this shot

preshot_description:
Reload 22408
SS NBI 70-350ms, SW NBI 210-350ms
Set Ruby time at 210ms
After 100ms, switch to Outboard fuelling only
postshot_description:
Good shot. Good beams.
No H-mode, but we don't want it anyway.
Density is a good repeat of 22408. Shot starts sawtoothing a bit later than reference
All TMP tripped at then end of the shot
Inboard Helios worked (at t=1s)

preshot_description:
Repeat
Shift Zref down by 1cm to avoid possible H-mode
SS timing 70-350ms, SW 210-350
postshot_description:
SS beam late by 23ms
Good repeat of previous shot

preshot_description:
Repeat
SS NBI timing 140-350ms
postshot_description:
SS has a notch at 300ms, SW breaks down at 250ms and does not come back
Lower density this time, perhaps due to the beams
No Ruby data
IB helios worked again

preshot_description:
Repeat
Reload impurity gas waveform from 22532
postshot_description:
SS has 1 breakdown, SW OK
No impurity puff
Ruby is back
Good otherwise

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description:
Good beams
still no impurity puffing

preshot_description:
Repeat	
SS cut at 210ms for poloidal rotation measurements
postshot_description:
OK
good beams

preshot_description: Repeat without SW
postshot_description: No NBI...

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: OK

preshot_description: Repeat	SS 0-350ms, SW 0-250ms
postshot_description:
Good beams.
Density slightly higher than previous shots

preshot_description:
Repeat
SS NBI 70-350ms
SW NBI 70-320ms
postshot_description:
OK
No Ruby data

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description:
OK
No ruby again

preshot_description:
Repeat
Remove HP gas puff
postshot_description: good shot, TS at last, no sign of an ITB

preshot_description: Repeat with NBI from 0.14s
postshot_description: shot OK, but both NBI late, SS only from 0.16s, and SW only from 0.29s

preshot_description: Reduce density to match #13694 using feedback control, beams from 0.07s
postshot_description: Only SS beam, good density control until 0.2s, higher density later despite gas flow being 0, but HELIOS puff is still on

preshot_description: Repeat for 2 beams, switched off t/b-HFS puffs completely
postshot_description: Good beams, disrupts at 0.3s, good shot, EF coil settings are higher than in #13695, no signs of an ITB, much broader velocity profile compared to #22554, H-mode from 0.2s

preshot_description: Repeat with NBI from 0.0s
postshot_description: Good shot, very similar to previous shot, H-mode from ~0.2s

preshot_description: Shift plasma down by 4.5cm
postshot_description: Good shot, still some signs of H-mode, very similar to previous shot, although dRsep is -2 cm.

preshot_description: Increase outer radius early on to match #13695, no LFS HELIOS puff (zero GAS9, deselect PV7)
postshot_description: Good shot, good radius match with #13695, still got H-mode

preshot_description: Match the fuelling, rather than the density from #13695, since previous shot has slightly higher density (as good as it gets with feedback). Switch to flow control, needed to enable GAS1 and GAS 2 beyond 0.1s, extend SW beam out to 0.35s
postshot_description: Good shot, very similar to the previous shot, gas waveform shifted 10ms earlier due to different timing of fuelling phases, prefill double of #13695

preshot_description: shift gas waveform, TS at 0.27s, cut-off SS at 0.27s for poloidal rotation measurements
postshot_description: Another good shot, fuelling change was in the wrong direction (SL is color blind). Doesn't make much difference though.

preshot_description: Repeat with SS beam only, correct FLOWREF
postshot_description: SS beam 50ms late, shot disrupts at 0.2s

preshot_description: Repeat to get SS timing right
postshot_description: SS late by 23ms, disrupts again at 0.21s

preshot_description: Restore fuelling from #22562, and repeat to get SS at t=0.0s
postshot_description: Good beam, still disrupts at 0.21s, less beam fuelling, leads to a locked mode probably.

preshot_description: Switch back to density feedback
postshot_description: good shot, very similar to 22562, not quite as hot as 13695

preshot_description: Repeat with both beams, enable outboard HELIOS again (GAS9, PV7), avoid TS time with gas puff.
postshot_description: Good shot, good beams, similar performance to 22562

preshot_description: Standard shot for counter. It has ELM coils waveforms in it.
postshot_description: OK but ELM PSU-B failed.

preshot_description: Reload 22476. No SW. SS from 50ms for 400ms.
postshot_description: OK, good beam. H-mode with some ELMs.

preshot_description: Turn on ELM coils at 1.4kA from 300 until 400ms.
postshot_description: Big locked mode at 220ms. One beam breakdown. ELM coil C started OK but tripped at ~320ms.

preshot_description: Increase puffing to try and get rid of the locked mode.
postshot_description: Good shot, good beam, but no ELM PSU B.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Good beams, bad plasma. Looks like still underdense. All ELM coils worked.

preshot_description: Increase fuelling again.
postshot_description: Good shot, good beams and all ELM coils worked!

preshot_description: Repeat and turn off ELM coils.
postshot_description: Beam breakdowns.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Good beams, but again there is a locked mode at 220ms, as in 22572.

preshot_description: One last repeat...
postshot_description: And again a locked mode at 220ms... So we give up on this.

preshot_description: Reload 22526, remove impurity puffing and use fuelling waveform from 22578. Put on ELM coils at 1.4kA from 300 to 400ms.
postshot_description: Good beam but ELM PSU A failed. H-mode with a few small ELMs.

OK.

Omaha timing good.

preshot_description: Again

preshot_description:

preshot_description: repeat with density feedback and increased ZipV gain.   I think that to make this work I will have to reduce the quad pre-amp gain on the HS coils
postshot_description: Full length (surprisingly). Some strange stuff in SXR signal (UFO). Reduced Z excursion.

preshot_description: retry
postshot_description: Full length.  8.4cm excursion.

preshot_description: multiply drive sqrt(2)
postshot_description: EFC 05 now failed (02 has not been working since 23161).  nb. ASM locked mode signals are completely misleading. No obvious signs of LM on raw saddle coil data, but sudden disruption nevertheless.

preshot_description: reverse sign of Z drive
postshot_description: pretty nearly full length. Distorted waveform on EF05, but at least something. 11cm excursion.

preshot_description: Standard shot (restore 23161).
postshot_description: OK but TF flat top starts only at ~50ms.

preshot_description: Standard plasma shot
postshot_description: Good repeat

preshot_description: Change to a more normal gas waveform

preshot_description: Restore EF settings from standard shot.  Boost gas input.

preshot_description: retry

preshot_description: Try a different scenario, 17772. Switch FA/AFPS selection
postshot_description: Good beam, plasma not much better. ANB data unreadable. Stays on c/c longer than original. Stored energy higher - beam earlier and probably higher power. Density and SXR about right.

preshot_description: Beam starts at 100 ms.
postshot_description: Late beam again.

preshot_description: Retry.
postshot_description: Only a very little late beam blip.

preshot_description: Retry.
postshot_description: No beams. SW NBI PLC lost and SS NBI is affected by the same PLC. Area entry needed.

preshot_description: PLC reset. Retry hoping for SS beam.
postshot_description: OK. Good shot, good beam.

preshot_description: Cut off NBI at 300 ms.
postshot_description: IRE at 175 ms, shot terminates at 230 ms. Beam didn't stop at 300 ms (incorrect setting).

preshot_description: Repeat, increase density by 10%.
postshot_description: Late beam, no IRE.

preshot_description: Retry.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Beam still late by about 50 ms.

preshot_description: Repeat.

preshot_description:
Change ZPGAIN to 0.6 (instead of 0.5).
Reduce density ref.
NBI from 70 to 170ms.

SS cut off just too early, before 100ms.

preshot_description: Repeat to get the beams right.

preshot_description: Reduce density reference by 40%.
postshot_description:
Beam started 20ms late.
Otherwise good shot. Disrupted at 335ms.

preshot_description: Repeat.

SS had several breakdowns and so fired late (at 115ms).
Early disruption at 120ms.

preshot_description: Repeat.

preshot_description: Retry.

preshot_description: Repeat and enable gas group 1.

preshot_description: Repeat.

preshot_description: Reduce current from 650 kA to 500 kA to try and get rid of the IRE and repeat.
postshot_description: Ok. This time we hit the flux limit.

preshot_description: Introduce plasma current ramp down after 350 ms to avoid abrupt termination. Shortened fuelling so that it terminates at 300 ms.
postshot_description: Ok. It looks like we have a shot with which we can work.

1 min

OK.

Repeat.
8 minute GDC after shot.

OK.

preshot_description:
Repeat.
15 minute GDC after shot.

Repeat.
Lower GDC reference voltage by 30%
2 minute GDC after shot.
postshot_description:
OK.
GDC tripped on first try.
Returned PSU1 to its original value: tripped again on too low current
Reduction of only 20%: still trips
Try increasing by 10% instead of reducing: tripped straight away
Last try: increasing by 10% manually when the pressure has settled after the initial GDC strike... SUCCESS!

preshot_description:
Repeat.
15 minute GDC after shot.
Manually increase GDC voltage by 10% (as in the successful attempt after previous shot).
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description:
Restore 21774 (we do scenario 2 first because CXRS needs a beam to check their calibration).  
- Put it in density feedback. Density reference at 0.1 at 0.220s
- ELM coils: start 0.30s, duration 0.15s, current 0.1kA (just testing)
- SS NBI: start 0.20s, duration 0.20s, voltage 65kV
- All 4 gas groups enabled.
- TS ruby timing: 0.35s
- XLP (Langmuir probes) timing: 0.25s
- GDC settings back to standard: PSU: 250,600,500,600, FLOW: 700.
postshot_description:
- RP probe lights up like a Christmas tree... and it shouldn't. Needs investigating.
- GDC has trouble striking. Pressure goes up very high (0.1 mbar) and pumps trip. Second try of the GDC after the pressure had normalised did work.

preshot_description:
Repeat.
Switch from Density to Flow control at 0.20s.
RP retracted by 10 more cm.
postshot_description:
OK.
- RP no longer touching the plasma
- NBI delivers full pulse
- soft landing
- GDC works fine

- ELM coils: start 0.30s, duration 0.15s, current 1.4kA
postshot_description:
Disruption at 0.40s, due to locked mode.
Density pump-out observed before the locked mode (which was not expected).
NBI ends 0.015s early.

preshot_description:

- ELM coils: start 0.30s, duration 0.15s, current 1.0kA
postshot_description:
No NBI.
No pump-out.

postshot_description:
Disruption due to locked mode.
No obvious density pump-out.

preshot_description:
Switch to scenario 1 (Ohmic).
Restore 23001.

preshot_description: Repeat. Delay the end of the density feedback by 50ms (330 instead of 280) to try to raise the density.
postshot_description: Good shot, good H-mode. The gas flood was not off because the SL is absent minded...

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: SW is fantastic. Longer H-mode period.

preshot_description: Repeat. Change TS Yag settings to try to catch the L-H transition with 1ms time resolution.
postshot_description: OK. H-mode started 19ms later and so missed the TS burst.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: OK. Good (lucky) timing between TS and L-H transition at 0.357s => nice TS data.

preshot_description: reload 23367 - 400 kA shot - set EFPS at 8 Ka from 150 ms - set zref = - 3cm at same time - restrict P1ps and EFPS
postshot_description: plasma shot ! - ran for 350 ms - cameras not great but get a plasma - seems to be a direct induction start up and not around P3

preshot_description: Repeat 0.4 MA shot with cameras, disable gas flood at the end
postshot_description: good shot density a little bit low, initial plasma current after merging is too lower than in the reference 23367

preshot_description: Increase CP3 voltage to 4 kV to increase initial plasma current, prolong current ramp to reach 0.7 MA, change to density feedback with t/b HFS-fuelling from 0.07s and disable LFS fueling from 0.1s. enable all gas groups
postshot_description: No difference in initial current, reaches flat-top shortly, but runs out of solenoid at 0.212s

preshot_description: Delay Ignitron start time from 4.9s to 5.005s to get the curvature of the filed right. Reduce CP3 to 3.3 kV compared to the previous shot.
postshot_description: Not much change in the initial current, but start-up looks better.

preshot_description: Delay P5 ingnitron start time to 5.01s and increase CP3 to 4.5 KV. Increase outer radius to 1.48m
postshot_description: No improvement in start-up.

preshot_description: Delay P4 ignitron start-time to 4.995s (-0.005s), adjust BV to reflect change, add SW NBI from t=0.0s, Increase shape to 1.2 for the flat-top.
postshot_description: good beam, not much change in start-up, flat-top lasts to 0.3s.

preshot_description: Delay P4 ingnitron start time to 5.005s (adjust BV and SHAPE accordingly), delay SW beam to 0.05s.
postshot_description: Start-up is clearly worse.

preshot_description: Revert to start-up of 23669 (best so far), delay Vloop to 0.003ms and increase early Vloop to 6V
postshot_description: Better start-up, bad handover, IRE at 0.24s

preshot_description: Increase CP4 voltage to 1.2 kV, matched handover, advanced IDIV =0.9 to 0.13, advanced SHAPE=1.2 to 0.13, modelled ZREF to keep P6 at 6 kA turns.
postshot_description: no beam, good ramp-up, better shape.

preshot_description: increase p4 voltage to 1500 - increase shape to 1.3- match to require BV - set zref = -4 for duration
postshot_description: good shot, better shape, but still touches CC, short H-mode period at 0.309 ms driven by the sawtooth

preshot_description: Increase shape to 1.5, tidy up Vloop to get a better match to BV, bring increase of outer radius forward by 0.02s.
postshot_description: Still at the CC, some handover problem (or instability) at 0.07s, second IRE during flat-top.

preshot_description: Decreased BV by 20% and set ZREF to -5
postshot_description: Disrupts at 0.125s, FA's at the limit of their capapbilities

preshot_description: Change ZREF from -5 to -3. match Vloop to measured values to get good control on ROUT
postshot_description: Wiggle in Ip at 0.07s, Ip slightly too low at handover, seems to be further off the CC, but ROUT is the same as in 23676.

preshot_description: Move handover (Ip,Rout) 20ms earlier to see if the oscillation is caused by the handover. Move plasma out by 2 cm.
postshot_description: event now clearly later than handover, plasma too big and still not off the cc

preshot_description:
Reload DREF from 23676, plasma router back by 2 cm. 
Decrease IP to 600 kA.
postshot_description: oscillation dissapears, but plasma still not off CC.

preshot_description: Increase Shape to 2 and increase outer radius by 1 cm
postshot_description: still sitting on the CC, closer to P3 as well.

preshot_description: repeat
postshot_description:
H-mode for 30 ms from 270 ms, with two ELMs. 
Plasma just slightly off CC.

preshot_description: Decrease shaping to 0.8
postshot_description: Shaping too triangular - still sitting on CC.

preshot_description: Increase shaping to 1.1
postshot_description: still touching CC.

preshot_description: Decrease Zref to -10 starting from 200 ms. Shaping equal 1.
postshot_description: H-mode Lost. FA currents lower than previous shot so could in principle lower ZREF further.

preshot_description:
reload shot 23683
increase density.  
incease DREF by 2cm
postshot_description: Oscillation returns.

preshot_description: Reload 23683. Change ZREF to -5 cm. Increase outer Rad.

preshot_description: Reload #23683, ZREF changed to 0
postshot_description: Plasma touching CC but only slightly.

preshot_description:

Convert to optical feedback.
NBI not yet ready, so ohmic.
Adjust radial feedback to match achieved ramp-up.

Plasma detaches at ~140 ms, huzzah!
Gets too big later on, limited by beam duct.

preshot_description:
Bring in DRREF from 1.52m to 1.47m.
Add SW NBI, as yesterday.
postshot_description:
Good beam.
Does not detach, quite.
No H-mode.

preshot_description: Move DRREF out by 2 cm, to 1.49m.

preshot_description: Move DRREF ramp-up earlier

preshot_description: Reduce I_p to 500 kA.

preshot_description:

No effect.

Finished with a great big MARFE.

preshot_description: Try again

preshot_description: Repeat

preshot_description: Repeat.

preshot_description:

Zero EF waveform.

postshot_description: Good shot. Density larger than reference. Plasma seems to be slightly shifted upward (non zero current in P6 and power load asymmetry on LP) even though better than yesterday.

preshot_description: Reduce flow ref by 50%. Shift Zref down to -1cm.

preshot_description: restore EFCC waveforms from 21297. No change to gas input.
postshot_description: Again remarkably good density, but no sign of locked mode.

preshot_description: restore EFC waveforms from 23773 (rotating correction) but moved 100ms earlier
postshot_description: EFc PSUs ran correctly.  Density good again.  Possibly some LM indication.

preshot_description: repeat with gas zero after 0.100s
postshot_description: density dropped obligingly.

preshot_description: Restore 21712.  Fix gas plant status to reflect that HU8 is now working tho not calibrated (HM4 still shot off).  Set Zref=0 throughout. Homer control NOT in use. Gas under flow control.  Enable AFPS1,2 instead of FA3,4. Load new TF pickup correction table to minimize TF pickup (affecting Z control). Ramp w/f to ECC and +8 to RP
postshot_description: SHot ran nicely. ECC A failed to energise.

preshot_description: Disable and re-enable ECC supplies. raise gas flow 15%

preshot_description: Repeat with probe 2 cm further inwards (R=175mm was are 195mm),  decrease fueling rate by 10% from 50ms onward

preshot_description: repeat with probe 2cm closer (R=155mm)
postshot_description: Good shot

preshot_description: Repeat to get the data

preshot_description: Repeat with probe deep into the plasma (R=145mm).
postshot_description: Density increase due to the probe interacting with the plasma

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Repeat to get shot

preshot_description: Boronisation recovery shot.
postshot_description: OK

Plasma probably still too low (looking at cameras).
Got 40ms of dithering ELMy stuff between 0.28 and 0.32s.

preshot_description: Change Zref to +0.6cm.

Lots of breakdowns on SW.
Lovely H-mode from 0.2s to 0.37s. +6mm seems to be the right Zref setting.

preshot_description: Repeat.

postshot_description: H-mode from 0.165s until 0.338 with a short interruption between 0.185s and 0.21s due to, neutron rate similar to #23524 which had 1 MW more PNBI, plasma is quite close to CC between 0.25s and 0.29s (ATM quality is not good, needs alignment).

Ran OK.

preshot_description:
Restore low current shot 17176.
Change FAs and AFPS settings to adapt to new wiring of FAs.

preshot_description: Change coupling parameters to optimal ones for optical feedback.
postshot_description: OK. No disruption this time. Overshoots on P6 current smaller than 2 shots ago.

preshot_description: Double ZPgain (0.8 instead of 0.4).
postshot_description: Disruption at the end of the current ramp-up.

preshot_description:
Restore 17176.
Copy Z category from 23885.
postshot_description: Disruption at 0.3s. Lost density feedback...

postshot_description: Good beam, OK plasma. ELMy H mode from about 0.240.  - some small ELMs around 260 ms

preshot_description: increase gas flow in first 100 ms from 8 to 11

preshot_description: increase gas to 12 (from 11) - decrease Zref to 0.3 (from 0.5)
postshot_description: some small ELMs, then ELM free than big ones.  Earlier termination than last shot, probably beta rose faster.

postshot_description: Not improved. NBI a little late. H mode is continuous though, which is good. Plasma terminated by 5kHz mode locking.

preshot_description: delay NBI start to 0.140.  Insert RP further.
postshot_description: No YAG data.  CO2 failed cutting out NBI at 0.320 (hence long shot!). 5kHz mode sustains at constant frequency after beam cutoff.

preshot_description: Go back to Zref=0.3(0.4)cm.
postshot_description: Rats. CO2 failed again - was perfect until a couple of seconds before the shot. Shot OK-ish.

preshot_description: raise i/b Helios pressure to 2.5Bar.
postshot_description: Excellent. Good RP data.

preshot_description: repeat with RP moved.
postshot_description: Good beam and shot.

preshot_description: standard plasma shot
postshot_description: Homer cut out, hence wobbly Bv and Ip. Density also a bit lower than reference during ramp up (boronised last week)

postshot_description: HOMER problem again

postshot_description: Good shot, NBI a little late (2 breakdowns)

60kV SW 1.3MW
ELM coils still connected

No BES, HOMER not working. SS beam very intermittent (picks up at 0.3s).
Plasma current OK at 0.65MA

postshot_description:
HOMER still failed
SW breakdown at 0.32
SS 1 breakdown at start

postshot_description: Good shot - good beams - good H-mode large event at 320 ms
