postshot_description: good beams but no H-mode - dont understand why not - XDC router reports a radius 10 cm larger but not in optical feedback

preshot_description: reload shot 27109 and cut gas at 250 ms otherwise no change
postshot_description: good beams - but not much better -still end up with a delayed H-mode and type IV ELMs

preshot_description: Increase gas in the period up to 180 ms to ensure enough density at 200 ms also turn on EFCC PF tracking algorithm
postshot_description: Type I ELMs are back - H-mode still ends at 300 ms

preshot_description: reload 27112 - cut gas at 220 ms
postshot_description: good beams and good H-mode

preshot_description: Cut all gas fuelling at 180 ms
postshot_description: Back transition at 260 ms - so missed the trigger - so too aggressive a cut in gas

preshot_description: Repeat shot 27113 with 1.25 ms between lasers
postshot_description: One break down in SS and one in SW  - type IV ELMS again after a delayed L-H transition

preshot_description: repeat to try to get type I ELMs
postshot_description: Good shot with regular type I ELMs - - TS trigger not in a complete ELM cycle

preshot_description: Relaod 26983 to try to get type IV ELMs - set laser 0.125 apart
Increase TS timing to 0.25 ms
postshot_description: Good repeat

preshot_description: Density f/b until 0.3. NBI from 0.150 and 0.200. 1KA in EFCC C and D. Restore RP w/f from 27118.
postshot_description:
OK shot, earlier H mode and reduced pumpout.  These ECC currents are probably not appropriate for this ECC configuration. ELM PSU A tripped (shot not affected)
Top notch density match with reference and 26951.

preshot_description: Put 1KA in all 4 ECC coil sets. Add gas after 0.300s.
postshot_description: OK. Density did recover with small ELMs, tho shot not much longer (nb coils-off shot 26951 stayed in H mode during Ip rampdown).  Plasma running on P3 coils especially towards the end of the shot.

preshot_description: Go up to 1.2KA in all ECC coils. Retain refuelling gas.
postshot_description: Crikey. Smaller ELMs during ECC activation with no pumpout and good long shot. Slow ELMs recovered after ECC during Ip rampdown.

preshot_description: Repeat with ECC off.
postshot_description: Hmm. Some non-sawtooth triggered ELMs and density higher than no-refuelling shot. NOTE gas input is being turned off at about 0.370 by PCS entering rampdown phase.

preshot_description: ECC up to 1.4KA. Con gaz.
postshot_description: OK  - loses H mode until refuelled.

preshot_description: ECC to 0.8KA on all coils. Con gaz.
postshot_description: OK shot. Density rises during extra gas.

preshot_description: 1.2KA on all ECC, halve refuelling rate.
postshot_description: HL after ECC come on. Recovers H mode after density is brought back up.

preshot_description: Increase density target before H mode, retain 1.2KA and halved refuelling rate.
postshot_description: Density increased obediently - slightly earlier H mode but not constant density LH. H mode density also increased roughly pro-rata. HL immediately after ECC applied (suspiciously).

preshot_description: Increase density target another 20%.
postshot_description: Density went up again but lost H mode and then shot following ECC application.

preshot_description: Start q scan. restore 27121, reduce TF to 0.48(0.52). ECC=1.0KA, with refuelling.
postshot_description: Dirsupts imemdiately when ECC come on (efit q95=2.8, reference continued down to 2.4)

preshot_description: repeat with ECC at 0.5KA.
postshot_description: Slightly earlier H mode and survived ECC - relatively fast ELMs.

preshot_description: ECC to 0.75KA each.
postshot_description: Pretty much the same as 27130

preshot_description: ECC to 0.875
postshot_description: Sudden death of plasma after ECC applied.

preshot_description: standard shot (4.5KV on P3)
postshot_description: Shot ran OK. Sawtooth driven H modes with dithery periods between

preshot_description: Try 26538 (p3=3KV) SS NBI from 0.050s. Disable i/b helios
postshot_description: Shot ran OK - looks like pretty low density. Should have used CHFS gas  -never mind can fix that.

preshot_description: repeat with CHFS gas set to 3.0s+0.250s, 200mBar.
postshot_description: CHFS failed to deliver, hence another low density shot. HXR alarm.

preshot_description: Replace CHFS with density f/b on LFS valves - will probably lose H mode and fast ELMs, but this should not affect CAE (we hope).
postshot_description: Density pretty well spot on. Plasma event at 0.310 causes severe density loss. CAE not observed. L mode.

preshot_description: Try for H mode - re-invoke CHFS gas. Retain density f/b at lower level to protect against HXR.
postshot_description:
H mode with fast ELMs returns. Density somewhat higher than 26586.
CAE diagnostic has LP filters fitted - hence no signal.

preshot_description: One last go at DI shot using ruby TS to assist breakdown (waiting for NBI), also extend prefill to 15ms (12)
postshot_description: Shot did run albeit with increased early density and reduced early Ip.

preshot_description: revert to 27140, with CHFS at 190mBar and filters off.
postshot_description: No NBI (sticky NGV, they say).  Density a bit low due to CHFS fill pressure.

preshot_description: Try again
postshot_description: Good - all systems OK. Fast ELM H mode. Density on the high side. Modes observed (phew).

preshot_description: Repeat adding SW from t=0.100 to 0.300. Disable ELM PSUs.
postshot_description: Good beams and shot. Extremely fast ELMs - if indeed they are ELMs. Density collapse about 0.260s caused by NTM.

preshot_description: Disable SW NBI and run with SS only. Reduce TF to 0.45(0.585).
postshot_description: Disrupt at 0.260s . No sliding joint warnings

preshot_description: retry
postshot_description: disrupt at about 0.210.  World first observation of anomalous Doppler effect using NBI (they tell me). Still no sliding joint alarms

preshot_description: Go down to 0.34T
postshot_description: even shorter shot.   Modes number obtained.  Now we have sliding joint warnings, max 151%, 70off.  Very nice data obtained. Possible Non-linear pitch fork splitting observed.

preshot_description: Go back up to 0.38T and enable SW beam with same beam times as SS.
postshot_description: Good shot.Second beams adds too much mhd.

preshot_description:
Go back to single beam ops for "cleaner" CAEs... 
Increase TF to 0.52T to exercise joints but also a valid data point in B scan.
BES data also to be taken.
postshot_description: Good data. Negative CAEs observed as expected.

preshot_description:
Repeat with 0.4 T and single beam. 
Expect positive mode numbers but less of the low end.
postshot_description: Nice data.

preshot_description: Raise B to 0.48T
postshot_description: Ok. No sliding joint alarms this time. Negative mode numbers observed and no positive as expected.

preshot_description:
Decrease to 0.39 T
Expect positive mode numbers.
postshot_description: Nice spectrogram's showing exact equilibrium between positive and negative CAE modes.

preshot_description: Try B=0.385 T
postshot_description: Good shot. Modes are shorter-lived  but nice spectral spread. (4-16)

preshot_description: Increase B=0.55T
postshot_description: Ok

preshot_description:
Try again B=0.38T for BES
SS start time moved to 75ms.
postshot_description: Better but modes still not observed in BES frequency range.

preshot_description:
B=0.395T  - finish B scan point. 
Change beam time back to 50ms
postshot_description: Ok. Modes not as prominent but nothing has changed...

preshot_description: Increase B =0.55T
postshot_description: Ok

preshot_description: Set B =0.36T
postshot_description: Ok. Modes as low as 500kHz and up to 3.7 MHz.

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: Ok.

preshot_description: Reload standard shot
postshot_description: Good shot

preshot_description: Reload 26870 - scenario 4 with rout = 1.46 m - increase IELM to 1.4 kA
postshot_description: Good beams and shot - get a dithering stage around 260 ms and then return to type I ELMS

preshot_description: Increase enable window of p4 and p5 to 0.7 s - cut gas at 230 ms to try to stop the refuelling of the plasma after the pump out
postshot_description: Effectively no H-mode - transits back to dithering stage before the coils come on

preshot_description: Increase gas in phase before 180ms as in 27112 in order to ensure enough density to get into H-mode
postshot_description: good beams - H-mode re-established - pump out triggered at 247 ms until 300 ms - the pump out in density results in a density similar to that in the previous shot which stayed in the dithery stage

preshot_description: Increase fuelling in the stage -from 180 to 200 ms to try to increase the initial H-mode density such that any pump out does not drop us below the L-H threshold density
postshot_description: Good beams - increasing the density kept the plasma in H-mode - stayed in a type I ELMing discharge and no density pump out (same as 27112 no coils)

preshot_description: reduce IP by 50 kA - reduce IDIV by 7 % to match
postshot_description: Two good beams - a shorter shot if anything - later L-H transition otherwise a very similar ELM period to the previous shot

preshot_description:
increase current by 50 kA relative to reference (i.e. 100 kA relative to last shot) 
increase Idiv by 7 % to compensate
postshot_description: Early strong H-mode get a much higher density but then back transition at 250 ms - probably due to a tearing mode

preshot_description: Reload 26848 - larger radius shot  but add extra gas as in 27168 - use early IELM time as in 27168
postshot_description: Good beams

preshot_description: Reload 27168 to see if it is reproducible
postshot_description:
SS one breakdown  - no effect of coils seen on the discharge
No density pump out but do trigger a few compound ELMs - the only  difference is the slight delay in the SS beam

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: Beams on time but no H-mode - fractionally underdense at the point of L-H

preshot_description: increase fuelling in period up to 185 ms - add a refuelling pulse from 250 ms
postshot_description: good beams - but everything else is bad! - a brust of ELmss is triggered which causes a dramatic pump out

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description:
L-mode. Flat top from 130 to 350ms and slightly higher than reference.
Nice non-linear TAE mode, frequency 100kHz, observed leading to up-down chirping indication existence of holes and clumps.

preshot_description:
Repeat but change beam settings: two beams: 
SS 70ms, for 80ms at max power
SW 70ms, for 400ms at 1.35MW.
postshot_description:
Ok. Second beam does not increase Te in early stage of the phase. 
No H-mode observed.

preshot_description:
Lower B-field to 0.5T (in a bid to increase diffusion and access H-mode).
Change duration of SS to 130ms.
postshot_description:
Almost no change in mode behaviour in the first 150ms. 
Short time intervals between chirps.

preshot_description: Deselect SS leaving only SW at 1.3 MW  and repeat.
postshot_description:
Ok. 
Time between chirps longer  - as expected.

preshot_description:
Set B = 0.35T
Keep everything else the same
postshot_description: ok. time between chirps gets smaller. Increased diffusion.

preshot_description: Enable SS  70ms, duration 130ms at 1.8 MW
postshot_description:
beautiful they tell me. 
two breakdowns on SS. SS starts at 120ms.

preshot_description: Repeat but raise B to 0.4 T
postshot_description: ok. Similar behaviour to last shot.

preshot_description:
Repeat keeping B=0.4T 
Disable SW and enable SS 1.85 MW starting at 70 ms and duration 400ms.
postshot_description: ok.

preshot_description:
restore #27179 (B field set to 0.5T)
Increase flat top current from  750 to 900kA.
SS 70ms for 80 ms 1.8MW
SW 70ms for 400 ms 1.3MW
postshot_description: Plasma unstable at 750kA in ramp up.

preshot_description: Repeat and change Z from 2cm to 0.0cm  to obtain H-mode.
postshot_description: Nice shot 950 kA . Run out of flux.

preshot_description: Try again with only SS for increased 400ms.
postshot_description: Not so lucky this time.

preshot_description:
Restore #27179
Change Z to 0.0cm 
Stop both beams at 130ms. starting at 70ms.
postshot_description: Good shot

preshot_description: Standard shot
postshot_description: Good shot though somewhat overdense as a repeat

preshot_description:
Reload 26976.
SS 150-300 ms, full power.
SW 200-400 ms, full power.
postshot_description:
Nice repeat; lasts longer than reference.
Good beams.

preshot_description: Repeat with all MSE channels enabled
postshot_description:
Good shot with MSE data (same length as reference).
First successful L-mode programme shot.

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: SW breakdown midshot, but data is good enough for PIC

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description:
Good shot.
This completes the L-mode scan.

preshot_description:
Reload 26935 (H-mode).
SS 100-240 ms, full power.
SW 140-340 ms, full power.
postshot_description:
Good shot, good beams; longer than reference with smoother density.
First H-mode programme shot.

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: H-mode arrived a little late - not good data for PIC

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: Good shot

preshot_description: Increase SS duration by 30 ms
postshot_description: Data not good for PIC

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description:
Good shot.
This concludes both the H-mode scan and the programme.

preshot_description: Reload 27175 scenario 4 - with ELM coils - remove the refuelling waveform
postshot_description: beam start time good - but SL forgot to change duration

preshot_description: Repeat and request full length beams
postshot_description: Good length shot and Beams - no evidence that the coils have any effect

preshot_description: Reload 26947 LSND  IELM=1.4 kA - set camera in fast mode to try to capture filaments during ELMs
postshot_description: Good shot - good beams - density pump out but then disrupts at 380 ms

preshot_description: Reload gas waveforms from 27127 to get a higher density version plus refuelling at 300 ms keep BT at 0.55 and IELM at 1.4 kA
postshot_description: Good shot with rapid ELMS - survives through to current ramp down

preshot_description: Repeat with IELM=0
postshot_description: Good shot - clearly shows effects of coils from previous shot

preshot_description: IELM=1.4 kA - increase BT=0.585T
postshot_description: Good shot - some effect on ELMs and density but less than at 0.55 T

preshot_description: Use IELM=1.4kA decrease BT to 0.52 T
postshot_description: Good beams - initial pump out but then reverts to normal ELMs

preshot_description: Use IELM=1.4 kA - BT=0.54T
postshot_description: Good shot - good beams - Not bad but not quite as good as 0.55 T

preshot_description: Use IELM = 1.4 kA - and BT = 0.56T
postshot_description: Good beams good shot - confirms that 0.55 T best

preshot_description: Use IELM = 1.4 BT = 0.55 T and remove end of shot refuelling - extend ELM coil current to 500 ms
postshot_description: density pump out less than 27204 even though no refuelling - less effect on ELM frequency

preshot_description: Reload 2720 - BT=0.55 T IELM=1.4 kA with refueling
postshot_description: ELM freq is same as 27204 but a lot less pump out

preshot_description: extend IELM to end of shot - reduce EFCC to zero at 300 ms and then ramp up at 350 ms to see if the EFCC have any effect
postshot_description: Large event at 270 ms disrupts plasma - 19 sliding joint warnings

preshot_description: Return
postshot_description: Shot ran but bizaree result - to be investigated

preshot_description: Retry
postshot_description:
Nice shot. Some dithery H mode around 300 ms.
Strange phenomenon during VDE that looks like an internal kink on the video - plasma briefly assumes a kidney bean shape while already out of vertical position.

preshot_description: Reload 26769 (first of two programme shots)
postshot_description: Density too high

preshot_description: Decrease FLOWREF by 15% throughout shot phase
postshot_description: About half of the needed correction; correct now until soon before150 ms.

preshot_description: Add step down in FLOWREF from 140 ms - reduce from 2.55 to 1.5.
postshot_description: Good match to 250 ms, still a little high after that, but close enough.

preshot_description: Repeat with moved RP for second and final programme shot
postshot_description: Good repeat

preshot_description:
Restore 25028, correcting PS changes in MCS parameters
 Reference => 25028.
postshot_description: Density systematically a little under reference, and more P1 swing used. This is due to running the shot ohmically at the PIC's request (reference had SS NBI). PIC is happy with the data, and this completes programme item (1).

preshot_description: Reload 26964 (cHFS 330 mB - enable gas group 10 in Central)
postshot_description: Density is systematically lower than reference - shoots up slower, then an MHD event throws much of it out at 170 ms.

preshot_description:
Attempt to reproduce reference density by other fuelling means:
1) Remove cHFS (i.e. disable gas group 10).
2) Turn on density feedback from 50 ms, matching reference waveform.
3) Add GAS11 and GAS12 from 50 ms.
postshot_description:
First sawtooth at 130 ms threw out lots of density... Then density feedback was always playing a losing game... Result: highly unstable repeated attempts to increase density following.
Was behind on density even before the sawtooth, so let's try ramping it up earlier.

preshot_description:
Add old-style IB Helios at 1000 mB.
Even out requested density ramp somewhat by moving midpoint.
postshot_description: First sawtooth problem again - and earlier this time, at 100 ms.

preshot_description: Slow the requested density ramp so that it takes nearly 300 ms to achieve full density. This is intended to test the possibility of making the shot last longer.
postshot_description: Shot is a lot more stable. It still struggles to reach the full reference density though.

preshot_description: PIC thinks that shot is hitting the same density limit as reference despite NELINT being lower. Request a slower density ramp.
postshot_description: Starting to look like a stable shot!

preshot_description: Scenario 3: (26791) - 2beams - PF Tracking feedback ON
postshot_description: Good repeat.

preshot_description:
Scenario 6: (26517) PF Tracking feedback ON
HFS (geoffs) from 100ms at 275mbar
postshot_description: Good plasma. Little overdense - will do a direct repeat without feedback.

preshot_description: Scenario 6: (26517) EF current feedforward
postshot_description: Good pulse.

preshot_description:
Scenario 3: (26791) EF current feedforward
(Geoffs HFS now turned off)
postshot_description: Surprisingly good - 100ms longer than 27228

preshot_description:
Scenario 5: (26364) PF Tracking on
HFS gas puff turned on
postshot_description: Locked mode. 50ms shorter than reference.

preshot_description: Scenario 5: (26364) EF current feedforward
postshot_description: No beam - not a valid repeat.

preshot_description: Standard Ohmic shot
postshot_description: 27 sliding joint warnings - all false. Density lower and H mode slightly better than reference.

preshot_description: Restore 26815. DND ELM-free H mode. CHFS gas at 220mBar. SS NBI from 0.200s (notional R=1.35, Z=0 throughout).
postshot_description: NBI late - 2 breakdowns. Density high and only short ELM-free H mode period. i/b gas plenum was too high - should have been 165mBar.

preshot_description: Reduce i/b gas plenum to 160mBar.
postshot_description: Not bad shot - major ELM event at 0.310 and seems to change state after that (MHD and then reduced Dalpha).

preshot_description: apply Vloop modulation on ff waveform but retain f/b as well. i/b fill slightly high, about 180mBar
postshot_description: Control system generated triangular Vloop waveform - lost H mode at 0.340.  Some hints of grassy ELMs while Vloop rising

preshot_description: Use ff only on Vloop during modulated phase. About 150mBar on CHFS
postshot_description: Ip drifting down during openloop phase. Faster ELMS during first couple of high Vloop periods.

preshot_description: revert to combined ff and fb control. Delay modulation to 0.300, NBI to 0.220. Increase modulation amplitude. 170mBar CHFS.
postshot_description:
Not much extra Vloop modulation amplitude. Remains ELM-free during modulation.
But, ski-ramp effect on density (nb Rout also slightly modulated)

preshot_description: Increase modulation amplitude
postshot_description: Tending to drop back into L mode during modulation

preshot_description: Intermediate modulation amplitude. Extend CHFS gas input by 0.100s
postshot_description: Stayed in ELMy H mode but no clear correlation between ELMs and Vloop. Densioty low - probably forgot to refill plenum.

preshot_description: CHFS to 160mBar. Remove one cycle of modulation.
postshot_description: More or less convincing.

preshot_description: retry
postshot_description: Goes ELM-free. Boo.

preshot_description: Try type III scenario. CHFS pressure to 0.270mBar. ss NBI from 0.060.
postshot_description: ELM frequency unaffected but density ramp significantly modulated.  Need to be aware that CO2 is over-sensitive to CHFS, and that Rout is being modulated somewhat.

preshot_description: Increase Vloop modulation amplitude.
postshot_description: Some effect but not what was intended.

preshot_description: Switch to a bit of scenario development.  Restore 27230 and add SW at 0.250, and z=+0.5cm (efit says reference has zmag=-5mm)
postshot_description: Not bad shot - ELMs slow and get bigger with 2nd beam.

preshot_description: Invoke ECC at 1.4KA from 0.220s. Configuration 24.
postshot_description: Went into slower ELMs earlier, then lost H mode around 0.330

preshot_description:
Restore 26531
Modify the ZDGAIN (0.4) and ZPGAIN (0.2). Adjust IP handover to smooth changeover.
postshot_description:
Good. Much faster ramp rate achieved. No IRE occurred.
Excellent ELMy H mode from 250ms to 400ms.

preshot_description:
Increase ramp rate to find IRE - change rise time to 100ms
Adjust VLOOP at 44ms and IP to improve handover
postshot_description: Two IREs present at 160 and 190ms. Shorter shot with a 250ms flattop. No H mode period this time.

preshot_description:
Repeat last shot and attempt to mitigate the IRE with a beam notch.
Select SW and adjust beam times.
postshot_description:
IREs mitigated with beam notch. Flattop 300ms duration. Brief ELM free H mode phase from 390 to 410ms. Density possibly too low to get H mode before this point.
Breakdown on SW.

preshot_description:
Repeat last. Swap beams over to get MSE data during startup phase to monitor q profile evolution.
Increase density by raising reference at 320ms.
postshot_description: IRE at 230ms. H mode from 330ms to 410ms. Good density match to 27251 either side of IRE.

preshot_description: Add second Ip ramp phase to mitigate the IRE to start at 85ms. Reach flattop at 150ms.
postshot_description: Mitigated first IRE in 27253, and moved second later in shot. No H mode. Duration 200ms. Good beams.

preshot_description: Restore density reference from 26531 and decrease rate of second current ramp. Aim to reach flattop at 200ms.
postshot_description: No IREs present. Discharge with duration 300ms terminating with a disruption.  ELMy H mode phase, some dithering, from 250ms. Good shot.

preshot_description:
Add second beam to try and increase the power during the H mode.
Select SW and add at the start of the H mode phase.
postshot_description: H mode present, but of similar quality to single beam shot (27256). Discharge terminates early compared to reference and H mode is slightly later. LLM not present in this shot, unlike 27251. Appears as though a tearing mode terminated the plasma.

preshot_description: Adjust the end of the second slow Ip ramp rate to reach flattop at 175ms.
postshot_description: Shorter shot, disrupts at 300ms. Dithering H mode.

preshot_description: Restore 27257. Deselect SW and move start time of SS back to study effect on the tearing mode at the end of the shot.
postshot_description: Good ELMy H mode from 350ms onwards. Discharge duration 450ms. H mode quality improved over reference. The long lived mode replaces the tearing mode which was present in 27257.

preshot_description: Repeat last with NBI start time at 150ms.
postshot_description: Good shot. Disrupts at 0.4s, flattop duration 200ms. Small ELMy H mode from 250 to 270ms.

preshot_description: Standard plasma shot.
postshot_description: Ok. Flat top 20 ms longer than reference.

preshot_description: Restore 26980 and repeat.
postshot_description: Shorter shot than reference, some MHD (IREs?) between 150 ms and 200 ms visible on the SXR seems to affect at least the density control. Runs out of flux at 323 ms. SS beam ok.

preshot_description: Repeat the same shot with SW beam added. Start at 200 ms for 200 ms.
postshot_description: Good shot. The density does not follow the reference at the beginning of the current ramp up.

preshot_description: Repeat 27267. One beam shot.
postshot_description: Good shot. No IREs this time. Still problems in controlling the density between 50 ms and 100 ms. SS beam ok.

preshot_description: Repeat 27269 (one beam). Change aim for BES.
postshot_description: Ok. Good shot. SS beam ok. Density feedback seems to be back on track.

preshot_description: Repeat with different BES aim.
postshot_description: Ok. Density feedback back to bad behaviour (density drop between 50 ms and 100 ms).

preshot_description: Repeat 27268 (two beams). SS at 150 ms for 150 ms, SW at 200 ms for 200 ms.
postshot_description: Disrupts at ~310 ms (looks like a mode-lock).

preshot_description: Restore 26969. SS at 100 ms for 140 ms, SW at 140 ms fro 200 ms.
postshot_description: Ok.

preshot_description: Repeat 27272 to complete the direct induction scan.
postshot_description: Ok. No mode-lock this time. Nice long shot.

preshot_description: Reload 26935 and repeat.
postshot_description: Ok. Shot longer than reference. drops out of H-mode at 240 ms when one of the beams is turned off and then back into H-mode again at 315 ms.

preshot_description: Repeat with different BES aim.
postshot_description: Ok. Closer to reference duration wise. Goes into H-mode at 180 ms and stays in H-mode all the way through.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: No H-mode. Not clear why because the shot is almost identical to the previous one.

preshot_description: Reload 27273 (L-mode shot) and repeat.
postshot_description: Ok. Good repetition.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: SW broke down. IRE at 310 ms.

preshot_description: Repeat 27277.
postshot_description:
Breakdown on SS. 
Ok shot.

preshot_description:
Restore 27051
Current ramp from 27257
i/b helios 9.94 / 20 1500mbar. Gas group 10 deselected on central screen. 
SW 150-250ms
SS 70-350ms
postshot_description:
Good beams. Good repeat. 
Not a good scenario - no h-mode
Plasma density not as high the PIC would like.

preshot_description:
Restore current from 24081
Change Helios fuelling 1500->1800mbar to increase density
postshot_description:
Good beams. Intermittent H-mode from 300ms.  Significant increase in density at end of shot. 
Not the shot we are after.

preshot_description:
Restore 27042 
Heilos off
SS 70 for 250ms
SW 150 for 170ms
postshot_description:
Higher density than reference - no h-mode
IRE at 220ms

preshot_description: SW start time changed from 150->120ms (duration 200ms)
postshot_description: Still have an IRE at 220ms.

preshot_description: Restore current category from 24081
postshot_description:
Good beams again.
Plasma killed at 220ms.

preshot_description:
Change track.
Restore 27171 - turn off ELM coils
Vertical kick -1.5cm (activated)
postshot_description: One beam.

preshot_description: Try again.
postshot_description:
Excellent shot!
Two breakdowns on SW

preshot_description: Move beam times forward to 100->80ms and 150->130ms
postshot_description: Not as good, brief H-mode.

preshot_description: Standard plasma shot.
postshot_description: Good repeat, dithering H mode present.

preshot_description: Restore 24523 from GC's prepared setup. IDIV waveform modifications to control inner gap. Reset i/b gas to 24523 settings.
postshot_description: Good beam. Reasonable repeat, but density slightly too high.

preshot_description:
Adjust FLOWREF downwards by 15% to move density back toward reference. Delay beam to repeat breakdown in original discharge.
Adjust ZREF up by 4mm to better match reference.
postshot_description: Density improving. H mode access now earlier, but density too high during this phase.

preshot_description: Reduce i/b gas by 10% to improve density match in H mode - reduce to 1800mbar.
postshot_description: Still overdense at the start of the shot. Suggests that either the prefill of FLOWREF is still too high.

preshot_description:
Modify FLOWREF to match standard ohmic, as this has a similar density to required (24523).
Add valve overrides (V1).
postshot_description: Density match appears to have improve prior to H mode. Still a little high in H mode phase.

preshot_description: Move plasma down to z=0.0 at 220ms (H mode onset) to increase ELM frequency and control density more.
postshot_description: Good match, little to hard on ZREF motion, causes rapid density drop.

preshot_description: Adjust ZREF to move to 2mm from 4mm at 220ms. Decrease i/b gas to 1600mbar.
postshot_description: Slight improvement on density match.

preshot_description: Restore 24542 from GC's prepared setup. Reset i/b gas  and NBI to match reference. See how well reference can be matched.
postshot_description: Reasonable repeat, good first try. Improvements possible on the density, and adjustment of ZREF.

preshot_description: Restore 27124. RMP shot with refuelling in FLOWREF. Enable spark gap at 180ms. I(RMP) = 1.39kA
postshot_description: Useful shot for AK.

preshot_description: Repeat last, but removing refuelling phase from FLOWREF. Move spark gap trigger to 250ms.
postshot_description: Good beams. Pump out seen.

preshot_description: Repeat last with I(RMP) = 1.0kA - find threshold.
postshot_description: Pump out still seen, threshold must be lower.

preshot_description: Repeat with I(RMP) = 0.8 kA. Add refuelling from 27124, decreased to 1/4 of the FLOWREF.
Repeat last, hopefully without radial oscillation - JS recommends adjusting BVGAIN/P54SGAIN handover 50ms later to reduce the effect.
postshot_description: Good, no radial control oscillations present.  Plasma current flattop last 50ms less than previous shot, just after a large rise in SXR at 300ms (touches P3).

preshot_description: Repeat after abort.
postshot_description: Improved duration, does not appear to rest on P3 anymore. Shot still shows large SXR signal.

preshot_description: reload shot 27298 - set zref =1cm till 220 ms and then 2mm thereafter
postshot_description: good shot - but ELM free and PIC wants some ELMS

preshot_description: Start SW beam at 150 ms (was 200 ms)
postshot_description: 2 Breakdown on SS and  1 on SW one ELM in the period but still  ears in the density profile

preshot_description: Add a zref step from 2 to 5mm at 300 ms
postshot_description: good shot - good beams

preshot_description: repeat
postshot_description: large pump out and then disrupts before the pellet went in

preshot_description: Reload scenario 4 shot 26870 increase gas in initial stage to ensure get into H-mode - add ELM coils at 1.4 KA from 240 ms
postshot_description: Good shot - good beams- no effect of the coils compared to the ELM off shot 26497

preshot_description: Relaod scenario 5 (900 kA) - move Zref from +1cm to + 2mm at 250 ms - add ELM coils reaching max of 1.4 kA at 300 ms - set SS at 50 ms SW at 180 ms use 1.8 bar IB gas puff at 994
postshot_description: good shot - good Beams and H-mode - from 250 ms - ELM free and then ELMs - difficult to tell if ELMs have an effect as there is no coil off shot

preshot_description: Scenario 6 - 600 kA With CHFS - SS start time 60 ms - SW at 250 ms
postshot_description: Lot of breakdowns on SW came on at 410 ms - get more ELMs relative to the one beam reference (26521) but the density is higher

preshot_description: Repeat to get two beams
postshot_description: two good beams - get an ELM free period with some type II ELMs in it then goes to type I - even though the coils are on - maybe higher freq than with coils off (27249)

preshot_description: Standard plasma shot - 25893
postshot_description: Good shot. Density ~20% less than reference. Dithering sawtooth driven H-mode 190-320ms.

preshot_description:
Restore 27067. 
O/H radius set 10cm from plasma. 
NBI south only start=40, duration=400ms
postshot_description: Good repeat. H-mode from 270ms.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: OK - but still unable to detect CII

preshot_description: Repeat. After pumping O/H system.
postshot_description: Good shot - noticeable difference in colour of puffed gas.

preshot_description: Modify Zref=1cm from 250ms, to keep plasma out of h-mode.
postshot_description: Good shot.

preshot_description:
Restore "hmeyer_Scen6_ECELESTE". 
Set up cHFS - 200mb
Add in second beam
postshot_description: Large amount of interaction with probe.

preshot_description: Retry with O/H moved out 3cm
postshot_description: Good shot.

preshot_description: Modify Zref=1cm from 117ms to keep plasma out of h-mode
postshot_description: Still went into H-mode. SW delayed - early breakdown

preshot_description: Increase Zref=2cm from t=117ms
postshot_description: Still goes into H-mode...

preshot_description: Load high collisionality shot prepared by HM. CH4 puff at 250 ms.
postshot_description: Ok. but late H-mode. Original shot had old inboard fuelling on.

preshot_description: Repeat with old inboard puff on.
postshot_description: Still late H-mode.

preshot_description: Repeat with different puff timing.
postshot_description: Ok. Impurity puff in H-mode.

preshot_description: Repeat with increased puff duration.
postshot_description: Ok. But not much CH4 visible in the plasma.

preshot_description: Repeat 27236 without CH4 puff for comparison.
postshot_description: Ok.

preshot_description: Load prepared low collisionality shot. CH4 puff at 180 ms. Duration 5 ms.
postshot_description: Ok, but again no CH4 visible from CELESTE 3.

preshot_description: Repeat with nozzle closer to plasma (760 mm).
postshot_description: Pulse ok. Not much difference from before.

preshot_description: Restore 27312. Shot with pellet.
postshot_description: Problems with interferometer and density feed-back.

preshot_description: Repeat after abort.
postshot_description: OK.

preshot_description: Restore rtefit test shot 16427.
postshot_description: Shot OK, but rtefit results very different to reference.

preshot_description: Repeat, with many faulty magnetics signals deselected.
postshot_description: Very encouraging rtefit results.

preshot_description: Restore shot 27204. Reference was a 2 beam shot, but only SS NBI available.
postshot_description: Shot OK, but pellet fired just before disruption.

preshot_description: Repeat, with ELM coil waveforms starting 30ms earlier.
postshot_description: Shot terminated too early.

preshot_description: Repeat previous shot with order of pellets swapped (medium/large instead of large/medium).
postshot_description: Late NBI, shot disrupts at 300 ms.

preshot_description: Standard Ohmic shot, i/b Helios at 1.8 Bar, 994+20.
postshot_description: Density a little low, H mode reasonable

preshot_description: Rely on PCS to enable PV10 (CHFS enable). Other gas selections bear little relationship between PCS and Central - strange. Set Plenum pressure to 200mBar. (went to 246mBar) . ONLY 1 NBI SOURCE AVAILABLE.
postshot_description: Good beam and shot. Regular 250Hz ELMs. No TM (thanks to only one beam), hence sustained until 0.380s. ELMs start about 0.160 - reference (2 beam) at 0.140. There is LLM - running at about 12kHz when sawtooth strikes.

preshot_description: Reduce actuator duration to 0.200(was 0.400)s. Plenum pressure now 0.200.
postshot_description: Gas shut off smartly at 0.230 (see DA/HM10/R) , but plasma lost density and H mode. almost immediately - shows that HFS gas actually assists H mode. Density was lower than previous shot due to reduced plenum pressure. nb There is almost no inner gap when CHFS gas is off.

preshot_description: Set CHFS duration to 0.250 and refill plenum from empty.  p=240mBar.
postshot_description: Same story - lost H mode immediately after gas shuts off.

preshot_description: Change p4/5 ratio to 0.85(0.7) to increase inner gap. Set Zref to 0.5cm(1.0).
postshot_description: Did sustain H mode after gas cut for a short time - then some violent event

preshot_description: Reload Ohmic scenario 1 shot 25967 - 400 kA  - ELM coil config 7
postshot_description: pump out at 265 ms  - Did not get TS profiels around the pump out because the trigger was left on the Yags and so missed the requried region - good RDC data - maybe something on rba - IR data

preshot_description: Relaod 26066 sceanrio 5 - 1 beam L-mode shot - turn off triggering on Yags and try to get data around the pump out time (245 ms)
postshot_description: good shot - good beam - all ELM coils fired - no effect seen on the density or other diagnostics as expected since this shot is aligned with odd parity

preshot_description: 2 BEAMS NOW AVAILABLE. Switch scenarios to 27202 (750KA). Zero gas flowref after 0.100, CHFS settings as 27329, fill 230mBar.
postshot_description: H mode slightly earlier (now into Ip ramp) though not so solid. Density collapse at 0.320 (LLM stops) , density recovers and H mode returns

preshot_description: Try for faster density ramp, increase pressure to 340mBar and shut off with 0.250s duration. Zero and deselect ECC.
postshot_description: Early density higher (and H mode perhaps earlier) but still dies immediately after gas cut.  Slow mode (2-4kHz) slows and locks.

preshot_description: retry
postshot_description: did survive gas cut for a while. H mode density somewhat lower and FIG pressure quite a bit lower than 27202 at this time.  We have a sustained slow mode and higher betaT during this phase.

preshot_description: Reduce SW beam durinag to 0.100s (end at 0.250)
postshot_description: Almost no change.

preshot_description: radical change of plasma shape (Rout, p4/p5 and Idiv)
postshot_description: Surprisingly not bad - sustained fast ELMs and longer shot that 27202.

preshot_description: Repeat 26517 (SS 50 ms+, full power)
postshot_description: Omitted CHFS gas puff, whoops

preshot_description:
Add CHFS at 200 mB.
Deselect ELM coils as a couple had gone yellow.
postshot_description: Somewhat more dense than reference - and has tearing mode that throws out density at 310 ms.

preshot_description:
Try to inhibit H-mode:
Move CHFS up to 300 mB, set ZREF = -1 cm (was 0).
postshot_description: Not a clear H-mode, but still some quiescent type behaviour is seen.

preshot_description: Move ZREF down to -2 cm
postshot_description: H-mode successfully suppressed

preshot_description: Increase CHFS to 450 mB
postshot_description: Big density jump

preshot_description: Reduce CHFS to 375 mB
postshot_description: Density more stable - MARFE does not occur

preshot_description: Increase CHFS to 410 mB
postshot_description: MARFE back - MARFE threshold is between ~375 and ~410 mB

preshot_description: Add SW beam (100 ms+, full power)
postshot_description:
General density level maintained for a longer shot, but quite variable on the smaller scale.
Locked mode seems to do a little less damage now.

preshot_description: Decrease CHFS to 375 mB
postshot_description: A more stable shot, but PIC still wants more density

preshot_description: Add FLOWREF from 100 ms on - drop to 6 at 100 ms, ramping to 12 at 500 ms
postshot_description:
SW breakdown - starts at 150 ms, not 100.
Nice long, very dense shot.

preshot_description: Double post-100 ms FLOWREF rampup rate, reaching max FLOWREF of 25 from 500 ms
postshot_description:
SW beam a bit rogue - breakdowns meant no input until after 200 ms, and the whole waveform shows a gradual decrease to the end of the plasma - rather strange...
ane_density peaks out at 3.5e20.

preshot_description: Increase FLOWREF ramp rate to reach maximum of 25 at 300 ms
postshot_description: Plasma died after 300 ms - loss of radial control.

preshot_description:
Return FLOWREF peak to 500 ms.
Turn off beams at 400 ms in effort to breach density threshold.
postshot_description: Disrupts at 300 ms again

preshot_description: Standard shot
postshot_description: Good repeat of standard shot

preshot_description: Reload DI shot (scenario 7)  26531 - use zp and zd gains from 27251 - use SS beam at 150 ms
postshot_description: good beams - good breakdown  - no IRE- but no sustained H-mode

preshot_description: Repeat - change handover to density feedback from 100ms to 150 ms
postshot_description: H-mode back - now looks more like the parent shot

preshot_description: Reload 27251 - DI with faster ramp rate and SS beam starting at 50 ms
postshot_description: Good beam - no early IRE - Hmode from 250 ms to 280 ms then back to L-mode

preshot_description: Add SW beam at 200 ms - increase vloop by 20 % in period form 15 to 50 ms
postshot_description: SS beam late by 23 ms - get an IRE at 170 ms - ELM free H-mode from about 270 ms - little effect of change in loop volts

preshot_description: Repeat
postshot_description: Good beams - but IRE at 170 ms causes disruption

preshot_description: Increase outboard radius by 3cm - delay SS to 150 ms and SW to 200 ms
postshot_description: IREs  at 160 and 190 ms Hmode from 290 ms

preshot_description: Reload Vloop waveform from 27251 to see if initial IP ramp is the problem - keep the beam late
postshot_description: still IRE at 170 ms - so not early current ramp phase

preshot_description: restore vloop from 27402 and improve current handover by adjusting feed forward waveforms
postshot_description: Good Ip ramp up - H-mode from 280 ms - SS 20 ms late

preshot_description: bring density feedback to start at 100 ms (was 150ms) start both beams at 150 ms
postshot_description: vertically unstable at 120 ms and disrupts

preshot_description: Repeat change the Zgains to the original setting
postshot_description: disrupts again

preshot_description: Switch to scenario 6 shot (600 kA) - set SS start 50 ms SW start at 120 ms - use 200 mbar in CHFS - zref = 1cm
postshot_description: Good beams - Hmode from 150 ms to 300 ms

preshot_description: Change actuator duration to 0,2 (was 0.4) to cut off CHFS earlier - set zref = 0.7
postshot_description: CHFS cut off at 230 ms - large n=1 event at 250 ms

preshot_description: return to full length gas pulse - increase outboard radius by 2cm to try to keep off cc more
postshot_description: H-mode to 350 ms - so by cutting beam get an extra 50ms of H-mode - would be good to turn the 2nd beam back on

preshot_description: reload LSND plasma with zref = -10 cm - use SS at 150 ms and SW at 280 ms
postshot_description: disrupts at 280ms - too near to Centre column

preshot_description:
reload 26887 (nb SS NBI power now higher). Density f/b. SS NBI from 0.150s. 
ECC coils selected but not driven. EFCC under programme control.
postshot_description: OK shot - generally similar, slightly lower Vloop, LLM looks much the same.

preshot_description: set P and D gains to 0.3 (had a step) and insert Zref waveform.
postshot_description: Loss ogf Z control at end of Ip ramp (before I changed anything) - this is a DI startup scenario so not unusual.

preshot_description: Delay X point formation by reducing Idiv around end of Ip ramp. Disable ECC (ELM A alarm)
postshot_description:
generally good. Realtime Interferometer signal went strange during later oscillations (looks like a lot of vibration)
FA1 tripped during last cycle. Slow Z drift. FA current=4KA-ish, V~50V pk. Strong coupling with Vloop (strange - using optical radial control).

preshot_description: Switch to gas flow control to avoid RT density problems.  Both beams,  same time.
postshot_description: FA1 tripped at 0.105s, no obvious cause

preshot_description: Increase D gain and try to balance Z
postshot_description: FA1 tripped at 0.105s, no obvious cause

preshot_description: Step up D gain and try again.
postshot_description: Better (didnt trip before oscillations) but still only 1-2 periods

preshot_description: Restore 26864 (2 beam scenario) - lose edit to Idiv.
postshot_description: Ran OK but bad event at 0.260s - NTM locked.

preshot_description: Small adjustment to Idiv. restore Zref from 27416, move 100ms earlier and halve amplitude.
postshot_description: Dammit - VDE at end of Ip ramp again.  Maybe it wasnt such a good idea to start the oscillations at this unstable time.

preshot_description: Delay oscillations by 0.050s
postshot_description: better but still not good - both FAs tripped at 0.210s, having reached -4KA previously.

preshot_description: Speed up oscillations to reduce FA current (and displacement amplitude)
postshot_description: realtime density failure - something wrong with CO2 control program.  This caused loss of beam.  But shot not that bad otherwise, thoyugh density was probably *2 too high (see Vloop and Dalpha). FA1 half tripped then recovered, then both tripped at 0.265

preshot_description: Change to flow control on gas, and put CO2 laser into manual.
postshot_description: Better - similar to 2 bean reference (27417, complete with event a bit earlier). Density a bit high. Lost both FAs at 0.250s.

preshot_description: Reduce demand to +/- 6cm thoughout. Hope event goes away.
postshot_description: Not bad.

preshot_description: Go for broke - make the plasma more unstable to get more excursion
postshot_description: Not too bad, lost control about 0.210, one decent excursion before control lost

preshot_description: Reload standard shot with ECEL from, Hmeyer prepared setup - nozzle at 730 mm
postshot_description: Good shot - ECEL fired - saw on Camera

preshot_description: Scenario 6 with two beams but SW cut at 250 ms - Add ELM coils from 25-0 ms at 1 kA
postshot_description: SL forgot to reduce the IB gas pressure - so got disruption at 100 ms

preshot_description: repeat setting 200 mbar in CHFS
postshot_description: good shot and beams - good effect on ELMs at 290 ms onwards

preshot_description: Increase IELM to 1.4 kA
postshot_description: Get a dramatic pump out and return to L-mode

preshot_description: extend SW to a full length beam since the Beta is now dropped by the coils  and reduce coil current to 1.2 kA
postshot_description: Good beams - still get too strong a pump out effect and then back transition

preshot_description: Start coils at 190 ms - flat top at 210 ms - decrease IELM to 1 kA
postshot_description: still get back transition - even though coils on earlier effect still occurs at the same time - but pump out may start earlier - big difference with 27428 is that initial density was higher in 27428

preshot_description: Increase cHFS pressure to 250 mbar- IELM at 1 kA  but start time as in 27428 i.e. 250 ms
postshot_description: SW had 2 breakdowns at the start - may have a small effect at about 320 ms

preshot_description: Reload 27410 - increase rout to +7cm to pull further off CC - set SS 150 ms SW 200 ms
postshot_description: pulls Off cc more but a lot of mode activity

preshot_description: return to Rout of 27410 - start SS beam at 0 ms as in parent (20101)
postshot_description: Oscillating density waveform - no H-mode access

preshot_description:
Shot based on 27037 (26500 with early high Zref + density feedback after 0.14s). Zref increased to 2 cm at [100,220] ms
Adapt outer radius to 1.43 m
Add ECELESTE waveforms.  Change puff start to  320ms. Valve V80 pressure 1496 mbar. Nozzle position 730mm. 
Beam times: SS [100,250] ms, SW [140,200] ms.
postshot_description:
SW didn't fire. 
No H-mode. IRE at 300 ms. 
Good density match up to 220 ms.

preshot_description:
Repeat with both beams with same settings. 
Adjust line-integral density trace around 220 ms. 
Ammend DRREF inwards by 1cm for better match of outer radius match. 
Move nozzle position to 750mm.
postshot_description:
Good shot. H-mode reproduced. 
One breakdown on SW. 
Event kills plasma at 320ms.

preshot_description:
Repeat. 
Push back ECELESTE Helium puff to 220ms for 100ms.
postshot_description:
Nice shot. Puff can be seen on camera from 220 ms. 
Puffing occurs through the L-H transition - nicely done. 
H-mode lost at 315 ms.

preshot_description:
Repeat with SW to 700kW. SS kept the same. 
ECELESTE clock to 100us.
postshot_description:
Nice shot. Beams ok. 
H-mode delayed by 10ms but still present despite lower SW power.

preshot_description: Repeat. Keep SW at 700kW (45kV). Reduce SS to 1.6MW (62kV)
postshot_description: H-mode lost - success.

preshot_description:
Increase SS to 1.7MW. Keep SW at 700kW. 
Change TS timing so that it's burst mode with 20 us between lasers.
postshot_description:
Good beams. 
Density much lower due to bad feedback on RT density.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description:
Good beams.  Good shot. 
H-mode re-established. 
Interferometer back.

preshot_description:
Repeat. 
Change TS times to cover L-H transition.
postshot_description:
Good shot. Good beams. 
Thomson data just before the transition.

preshot_description:
Restore low density shot. 
Keep beam times from previous shot.
postshot_description:
Interlock on SS terminates beam around 140 ms. 
Brief H-mode periods.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description:
Ok. Shot ran through.  Interferometer back. 
Extended dithering at transition.

preshot_description: Repeat. De-sable SW.
postshot_description: Ok. Brief sawtooth-induced H-mode.

preshot_description:
Repeat. Change beams: 
SS reduced to 1.4MW. (58kV)
SW 800kW (45kV)
postshot_description:
Good beams.
Brief H-mode still.

preshot_description: Restore standard plasma shot 25893
postshot_description: Good repeat.

preshot_description:
Repeat 25967 - Scenario 1 Ohmic 400kA, I_ELM=1.4kA
TS timing set to start=18ms, interval=2ms
postshot_description:
Good plasma. Density slightly higher during first 100ms and from 280ms onwards.
Small density pump-out observed cf. reference.

preshot_description:
Restore 27428, Ip=600kA with I_ELM=1kA
TS timing reset to standard setting of start=1ms, interval=4.33ms
postshot_description: Short beams due to real-time density failure (protection system reports beam-dump over-temperature)

preshot_description: Repeat previous with I_ELM=1.4kA
postshot_description: Good beams... Density pump-out observed during ELM coil period. ELM-control observed.

preshot_description: Restore 27442. Restore density waveform from 27205. Switch gas control mode to FLOW_REF at 280ms.  set FLOW_REF reference to 6e21/s from 280-500ms.
postshot_description: Still get density oscillations in period 230-350ms. Good beams, not getting into H-mode.

preshot_description:
Repeat. Switch to FLOW_REF earlier @230ms and increase FLOW_REF to 7e21/s.
Restore DRREF waveform from 27441. Increase IDIV points by +3kA from 130ms onwards.
postshot_description: Better density, still get a droop after 250ms, stays on centre column till ~250ms. No H-mode.

preshot_description:
Repeat with following changes:
Bv decreased from 250ms onwards and IDIV point at 250ms increased, to match achieved levels in last shot. Switch from density feedback to FLOW_REF at 180ms, FLOW_REF=7e21 from 180ms onwards. SW beam start time changed to 150ms, duration of both beams increased (SS=600ms, SW=450ms).
postshot_description: Good beams. Density trace is much improved - pretty much flat from 230ms onwards. Still no H-mode!

preshot_description:
Restore 27409. Reduce Zref to zero and square wave pulse burst added from 200ms - 450ms. Tau(gap)=20ms, Tau(kick)=10ms, amplitude =+1cm, baseline=0cm.
CHFS plenum pressure ~200mb.
postshot_description: 1 BD on SS beam. ELM bursts observed immediately following each Z kick.

preshot_description:
Try again...
CHFS gas plenum at ~256mb
postshot_description: Good plasma, good beams.  ELM bursts correlated in anti-phase with the kicks cf. previous shot.

preshot_description:
Repeat 27470 with double the kick frequency.
CHFS gas plenum at ~200mb
postshot_description: Good plasma, good beams. No modulation of ELMs observed.

preshot_description:
Repeat 27470 with no Zkick and VLOOP modulation restored from 27247.
CHFS plenum ~260mb.
postshot_description: Good plasma, good beams. Effect of Vloop modulation evident in I_SOL and Ip trace.

preshot_description: Restore 25997
postshot_description: Camera didn't trigger.

preshot_description: Retry - reduce flowref by 15%

preshot_description: Repeat.

preshot_description: Repeat hoping for better beams.

preshot_description: Repeat to try for 2 beams, TS set into correct mode (left in this mode from last nights experiment).
postshot_description: SW beam too long (operator oversight) since not set to short pulse. Ok otherwise.

preshot_description: Repeat to get the right duration.
postshot_description: Good shot, though still a little shorter than reference.

preshot_description:
Fill cHFS plenum with 400 mbar
Repeat

preshot_description: Repeat.

preshot_description: Reload 29470 and repeat.
postshot_description: Ok, good shot.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Ok, good repeat.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Ok Good repeat again.

preshot_description: Repeat.

preshot_description: Restore 29604, ELM coils de-selected. SW from 50ms. EF control set to "PF tracking". Activate Z-kick trigger. Change ZD/PGAINs to give increased response around time of vertical kick . cHFS at 259mb.
postshot_description:
Looks good, got kicks but EF in PF track mode doesn't appear to have changed time of NTM onset. density is a touch low up until the first NTM kick - need to match cHFS plenum pressure better!
One of the FAs tripped during high gain phase

preshot_description: Load prepared setup mast_sl/T&C-013-900kA: ref 28787 with LFS fuelling and density feedback matching 29763, Zref=2cm.
postshot_description: Good plasma, disrupted at ~340. Density diverges from reference from about 180 (overdense cf 29763), gas valves are closed at this time and no HFS fuelling selected so it's unclear where the density rise is coming from. Plasma is sitting on centre column which could be causing a bit of extra fuelling.

preshot_description: Repeat previous shot with different DBS/BES settings. DRREF changed to +3cm after 200ms.
postshot_description: Lower density about 10% above target, but still looks quite close to the CC.

preshot_description:
Reload 29094 - LSND 600 KA ,modify Zref from -17 to -19.2 for PCS recompile - increase  density in first 180ms then cut gas -= leave in density feed back from 250 ms 
SS request at 100 ms SW at 177 ms

SW late (start time 240ms) - density falls from 200 ms onwards and then H-mode from 
300 ms - need to get the H-mode earlier

preshot_description:
start SS at 70ms request SW start at 150ms (i.e. expect 173ms)
add RMPS with 1.0 kA from 350 ms - set LFS radius at 1.4 m from 200 ms onwards 
Extend gas fuelling to 200 ms
postshot_description: SW had series of breakdowns - H-mode from 330 ms  - can see the pump out due to the coils

preshot_description: repeat to get both beams - allow Pellet at 480 ms

preshot_description: move density feedback start from 250 ms to 200 ms  - repeat to get 2nd beam
postshot_description: SW started at 220 ms plasma disrupted at 250 ms  - event at 155 ms drops density

preshot_description: delay SS start to 100 ms
postshot_description: disrupts at 180 ms  - again due to locked mode

preshot_description:
reload 29507 -limit AFPS2 to 1.2 KA - set SS at 50 ms set SW at 260 (request 237 ms)
set HFS to 1.8 bar - 994 start

preshot_description: Repeat with ELM coils start time of 270ms - 1kA

preshot_description: Reload 30013  to get SW to start at 260 ms

preshot_description: repeat

preshot_description: repeat - removing feedback on density
postshot_description: good shot - higher density than previous probably due to wall loading

Bt=0.58T

OK. 
IRE at 180ms.

preshot_description: Repeat.

preshot_description: Repeat.

reload 29227 scenario 1 400 kA CDN - use IELMA,B = 1.0

ELM coils lead to back transition at 320ms.
Type II ELMs appear to have been removed, rather than enhanced.
All ELM coils fired.

Restore IDIV from 29699 to move strike point nearer to DSF
cHFS fill at 210 mbar

preshot_description: Restore 30389. Increase Ip waveform to 0.7MA at 0.57s. Extended all ELM power supply waveforms to 0.6s.
postshot_description: SW breakdown at 0.14s. Shot disrupts unexpectedly. Reason unknown.

preshot_description: Repeat 30397.
postshot_description: Still not working right.

preshot_description: Restore 30396. Increase ZREF to -0.7cm. SS beam start at 0.1s and SW beam starting at 0.127s.
postshot_description: Good repeat. Beam breakdowns in SS and SW at 0.14s.

preshot_description: Repeat 30390. Delay cHFS by 0.09s. SS beam start at 150ms and SW beam at 200ms.
postshot_description: SW beam breakdown at 0.21s.

preshot_description: Restore 30389. Increase Ip=0.7MA at 0.57s. SS beam start at 0.1s and SW beam start at 0.117s.
postshot_description: Ip ramp up wasn't as large as hoped for but shot useful.

preshot_description: Repeat 30405. Change SW beam start time to 0.1s.
postshot_description: SW beam breakdown at 0.15s. Plasma disrupts before pellets go in.

preshot_description: Repeat 30407.
postshot_description: Good beams but shot still disrupts too early.

preshot_description: Restore 30356 and convert to use HOMER radial position control. Zero DRREF. SS beam starting at 0.1s.
postshot_description: Plasma radius was too large.

preshot_description: Restore 30409. Scale FLOW_REF by 1.3.
postshot_description: SW beam had breakdown at 0.12s. Shot still disrupts at 0.3s.

preshot_description: Restore 30410. Restore GAS category from 30148.
postshot_description: No change.

preshot_description:
Restore 30384 - investigate mitigation in scenario 3 with n=6
Set south 100ms start
Set SW 117ms
postshot_description:
Not as desired - well matched in density but H mode short and late.
SW breaks down after starting. Shot ends early at 0.350ms.
All ELM coils fired.

preshot_description:
Repeat 30384 with I(ELM)=1.0kA
Raise to BT=0.585T.
Try for full beams.
postshot_description:
Good shot, good beams.
H mode from 280ms to end of shot at 0.6s
Slightly later (50ms) entry into H mode than reference.
Mitigation seen during coils on phase, once ramped to full current (~400ms)

preshot_description:
Reload 30271 - scenario 8 mitigation with n=6
Set I(ELM) = 1.2 kA
South 150 ms
SW 177 ms
postshot_description:
H mode from 270ms to 620 ms. Back transition 450ms to 480ms.
High frequency ELMs from 400ms when coils reach full current.
All ELM coils fired.

preshot_description:
Restore 30417 - raise ELM coil current to 1.2 kA
South 100 ms
SW 117ms
postshot_description:
Good shot - SW slightly later than requested.
H mode from 280ms, with mitigation when coils reach full current at 400ms
No back transition seen.
All ELM coils fired.

preshot_description:
Restore athorn intrinsic rotation
Reload of 30117 using density from 29991 adjusted to be 30% higher
Upshifted 700kA shot.
Ohmic (deselect South), no i/b gas.
postshot_description: runs out of flux before reaches required density - wanted a line integrated density of ~2.1x10**20 - only achieved 1.5x10*20

preshot_description: Reload Scenario 3 based on 30419 - increase IELM to 1.4 kA bring start 20 ms earlier
postshot_description: good shot with good beam -all ELM coils fired

preshot_description: restore shot 30399 scenario 4 for DBS measurements
postshot_description:
Good beams.
H mode from 0.2 to 0.380s

preshot_description: Repeat previous with different DBS settings
postshot_description: Good shot - good repeat  - nice regular ELMS

preshot_description: reload 30421 - IP ramp up  from 600 at 400ms to 700 kA at 500ms
postshot_description: good beams - good ramp up of current until flux runs out at 450 ms

preshot_description: restore from Lgarzot set up file based on 22664 - modify max P2 to 14 kA set P1ps limit to 40 kA - TF = 0.605 T SS = 74 ms SW 100 ms Note zref=-1.2 cm
postshot_description:
good beams - H-mode from 280ms  
X_MM_LVPS shows a lot lower current than AMC_TF - TF does not reach flat though

preshot_description: repeat - bringing TF start time 200 ms earlier
postshot_description: good shot TF now reaches flat top

preshot_description: repeat IP=910 TF=0.624 T
postshot_description: good beam - good shot - TF resistance OK BUT did not reach more 87 kA

preshot_description: Reload 29261. N puff at 195 ms.
postshot_description: Ok. As reference. N observed.

preshot_description: Reload 29275. N injection at 255 ms. Move ZREF in H-mode phase from -1 cm to -1.1 cm.
postshot_description: Ok. Good shot. N injected. Smaller ELMs than in reference shot.

preshot_description: Reload 29417. Increased duration of impurity puff by 10 ms. 600 kA, only one beam.
postshot_description: Ok, nice long shot. N injected. Underdense with respect to reference.

preshot_description: Repeat.
postshot_description: Good shot.

preshot_description: Repeat, with SS NBI. S file generation on.
postshot_description: Shot terminated early at 240ms, but coils ran on after. This is a rtefit PCS bug.

preshot_description: Repeat with SEG01_GP and SEG12_GP isoflux proportional gains reduced to 10.
postshot_description: Shot terminated at 320ms, but may be useful.

preshot_description: Restore shot 30383 for MHD-012. Changed timing of ZREF kicks with respect to reference.
postshot_description: Ok.

preshot_description:
reload scenario 6 1 beam SS at 50 ms - correct chfs - set zref = -0.55 -(same as 29471) 
set rout = 1.48m as in 28118 use IELM = 1kA in A+B 0.7 KA i C+D from 250 ms
postshot_description: no real time density so shot flooded with gas

preshot_description: Reload 30366. TF settings as in 29301 after changing plant limits.
postshot_description: Ok. Good shot.

preshot_description: Reload 30377 and TF settings as in 29301.
postshot_description: Ok, although shorter than reference, probably due to the lower TF.

preshot_description: Repeat with TF settings as in 29341. Very low TF (0.3 T).
postshot_description: Ok. Dies very early, but late enough for the purpose of the experiment..

preshot_description: reference shot uses CHFS gas at 200mBar
postshot_description: ran OK, density a bit low, intermittent H mode, AE modes observed OK.

preshot_description: replace CHFS gas with LFS gas, retime YAG TS
postshot_description: Shot a bit shorter mostly due to lack of H mode. Density roughly on track until reference went H mode.  CAE only observed very briefly

preshot_description: raise gas 20%
postshot_description: density increased and shot a bit longer but modes failed to reappear

preshot_description: revert to CHFs gas with D2 to check nothing has changed.
postshot_description: miserable shot, but modes OK

preshot_description: Refill main LFS plenum with H2.
postshot_description: Too much H2 - modes disappear.

preshot_description:
Decrease the Hydrogen amount.
Move switch to flow ref phase 120ms earlier. Add prefill to flow ref phase. Adjust timing of cHFS to suit.
Halve duration of flow ref.
cHFS 210 mbar fill (D2)
postshot_description:
Duration similar to previous.
More deuterium seen in the plasma this time.

preshot_description:
Repeat the previous with neutron camera in new position.
cHFS 210 mbar
postshot_description: Good repeat - H mode from 140 to 190ms. ELMy.

preshot_description:
Restore 30458 to increase hydrogen level.
cHFS 210 mbar
postshot_description: No beam - calorimeter gate not opened.

preshot_description:
Repeat last after missing beam.
cHFS 213 mbar
postshot_description:
Good repeat. H mode present, good beam.
Type III ELMs followed by type I

preshot_description:
Return to lower hydrogen level shot
Restore 30459
Require higher density - raise cHFS pressure to 256 mbar.
postshot_description:
H mode from 150ms to 190ms.
Only a small effect on the density - H mode phase there is little difference in density to the previous shot.

preshot_description:
Raise the level of hydrogen in the plasma to give an intermediate.
Adjust flow ref in 30459 out to 82ms.
Drop cHFS to previous level (210 mbar): cHFS 210 mbar fill
postshot_description:
Good beam.
Good repeat. H mode 140ms to 190ms as reference.

preshot_description: Repeat last shot with new neutron camera settings.
postshot_description: Good repeat.

preshot_description:
Restore 30459 - now starting shot with deuterium and adding H2 with cHFS from 80ms on.
chfs 230 mbar H2.
postshot_description: Good repeat, however modes disappeared.

preshot_description:
Repeat with new neutron camera position.
cHfs 190 mbar.
postshot_description: Two times lower DD neutron rate than reference 30457. Highest hydrogen concentrations.

preshot_description:
Repeat with new neutron camera position.
cHFS 164 mbar.
postshot_description:
Good beam.
Good repeat.

preshot_description:
Repeat with increased beam power (74 kV)
cHFS: 184 mbar
postshot_description: Good shot. Modes present.

preshot_description:
Repeat last using hydrogen in outboard and cHFS gas plena.
cHFS 181 mbar.
postshot_description: No HF gas.

preshot_description:
The last plasma:
Convert to i/b Helios 1724 mbar fill and repeat
Stop beam at 140ms, beam at 70kV.
postshot_description: Good shot.
